{"type":"text","timestamp":1782925209384,"sessionID":"ses_0e161eb7effeWxawnzJ6Yp6rgG","part":{"id":"prt_f1e9f879c0014gOZLaMDXQj3cF","messageID":"msg_f1e9f5e4a001KB5tV9osq7A3VZ","sessionID":"ses_0e161eb7effeWxawnzJ6Yp6rgG","type":"text","text":"Setup bindings emitted below. Now gathering independent evidence across all 6 clusters in parallel.\n\n```\nBINDING: review_target=.opencode/specs/deep-loops/031-deep-loop-issues-with-gpt-opencode/015-skill-doc-drift-remediation\nBINDING: review_target_type=spec-folder\nBINDING: review_dimensions=all\nBINDING: spec_folder=.opencode/specs/deep-loops/031-deep-loop-issues-with-gpt-opencode/015-skill-doc-drift-remediation\nBINDING: execution_mode=AUTONOMOUS\nBINDING: lineage_mode=auto\nBINDING: artifact_dir=.opencode/specs/deep-loops/031-deep-loop-issues-with-gpt-opencode/015-skill-doc-drift-remediation/review/lineages/glm-max\nBINDING: session_id=fanout-glm-max-1782925103545-7vw78n\nBINDING: executor=cli-opencode model=zai-coding-plan/glm-5.2\nBINDING: stopPolicy=max-iterations\nBINDING: maxIterations=5\nBINDING: convergenceThreshold=0.1\n```","time":{"start":1782925199260,"end":1782925209382}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782925209417,"sessionID":"ses_0e161eb7effeWxawnzJ6Yp6rgG","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"call_b4eda93d4ab4414bb314ae71","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"echo \"=== CLUSTER 5: plugins/README.md entrypoint count ===\"\nrg -n -- \"[Ss]ix|[Tt]hree|[0-9]+ plugin|[Ee]ntrypoint|mk-deep-loop-guard\" .opencode/plugins/README.md 2>/dev/null\necho \"\"\necho \"=== CLUSTER 5b: actual plugins dir listing ===\"\nls -1 .opencode/plugins/*.js 2>/dev/null\necho \"\"\necho \"=== CLUSTER 4b: deep-improvement TOML references in docs ===\"\nrg -rn -- \"\\.toml\" .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/ 2>/dev/null | rg -iv \"node_modules\" | head -30 || echo \"(zero .toml hits in deep-improvement)\"","workdir":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public"},"output":"=== CLUSTER 5: plugins/README.md entrypoint count ===\n2:title: \"OpenCode Plugin Entrypoints\"\n3:description: \"Six plugin entrypoint files OpenCode auto-loads at startup. Helper bridge modules live with their owning skills, not in this folder.\"\n6:# OpenCode Plugin Entrypoints\n8:OpenCode 1.3.17+ auto-loads JavaScript files in `.opencode/plugins/` at session start. This folder is intentionally limited to those entrypoint files so helper modules cannot be mistaken for plugins. Helpers and bridges live alongside their owning skills under `.opencode/skills/.../mcp_server/`.\n16:- [3. CURRENT ENTRYPOINTS](#3--current-entrypoints)\n36:1. Create the entrypoint here (`my-plugin.js`) with a **default export only** — no named exports (every named export is loaded as its own plugin; see Overview). Attach any test surface as a property on the default function.\n50:| `mk-deep-loop-guard.js` | Detection-layer `tool.execute.before` plugin for Task-tool dispatches targeting deep-loop sub-agents. Flags (default) or blocks (`MK_DEEP_LOOP_GUARD_REJECT=1`) a Deep Route header whose declared `mode` disagrees with `mode-registry.json`'s entry for the actual `subagent_type` being dispatched. Fails open on registry read errors. |\n63:This keeps plugin entrypoints minimal and lets owning skills own their bridge contracts.\n150:- `.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/hooks/` — sibling hook entrypoints (different runtime contract)\n\n=== CLUSTER 5b: actual plugins dir listing ===\n.opencode/plugins/mk-code-graph.js\n.opencode/plugins/mk-deep-loop-guard.js\n.opencode/plugins/mk-goal.js\n.opencode/plugins/mk-skill-advisor.js\n.opencode/plugins/mk-spec-memory.js\n.opencode/plugins/session-cleanup.js\n\n=== CLUSTER 4b: deep-improvement TOML references in docs ===\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/changelog/v1.5.0.0.md:- `.codex/agents/improve-agentn` → `.codex/agents/deep-improvementn`\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/changelog/v1.17.0.0.md:Every agent is authored once under `.opencode/agents/<name>.md` and mirrored to `.claude/agents/<name>.md` and `.codex/agents/<name>n` so each runtime ships the same behavior. Editing one copy without the others makes the runtimes silently disagree. A new `scripts/check-agent-mirror-sync.cjs` wraps the existing `verifyMirrorSync` library and turns it into a gate: given the changed agent files (or `--all`), it fails when any agent's mirrors drift from its `.opencode` canonical body — including a deleted mirror, or a deleted canonical whose runtime copies still linger. It is wired changed-files-scoped over added, modified, and deleted agent paths into `.opencode/hooks/pre-commit` and into a new `.github/workflows/agent-mirror-sync.yml` that fails closed if the checker is ever removed, so the divergence is caught at commit and pull-request time instead of in production. This promotes the mirror check from a deep-improvement promotion-only gate to an every-commit and every-PR gate.\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/changelog/v1.17.0.0.md:A gate that runs on every commit has to be precise, and the old normalizer was both too loose and too narrow. Each runtime mirror legitimately describes itself — a clause along the lines of \"this runtime's mirror; the canonical source lives in .opencode\" — and refers to its own runtime agent-file path (for example `.codex/agents/<name>n`), neither of which the canonical file carries. The old `normalizeRuntimeSpecificText` in `scripts/lib/mirror-sync-verify.cjs` counted the self-description clause as body drift and false-flagged healthy mirrors, while a blanket rule that collapsed every bare `.md`/`n` extension token was loose enough to mask a real format-extension mismatch. The normalizer now strips the self-description clause and normalizes only the runtime agent-file paths — so a mirror's reference to its own `.codex/agents/<name>n` no longer reads as drift — and the blanket bare-extension collapse is gone. The fix is deliberately conservative: it removes only the known self-description and agent-path shapes, and real body drift, including a genuine format-extension mismatch, is still caught.\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/changelog/v1.17.0.0.md:- `.codex/agents/contextn` — restored the dropped Tool-Inventory row to match the canonical agent body.\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/assets/agent_improvement/target_manifest.jsonc:      \".agents/commands/speckit/handovern\",\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/assets/agent_improvement/target_manifest.jsonc:      \".agents/commands/speckit/handovern\",\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/changelog/v1.0.1.0.md:| `.codex/agents/agent-improvern` | Modified | Mirror sync, wording fix |\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/scripts/shared/promote-candidate.cjs:    || /^(\\.\\/)?\\.opencode\\/agents\\/[^/]+\\n$/.test(normalized);\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/manual_testing_playbook/08--agent-discipline-stress-tests/setup-cp-sandbox.sh:require_path \"${FIXTURE_ROOT}/.opencode/agents/cp-improve-targetn\"\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/manual_testing_playbook/08--agent-discipline-stress-tests/setup-cp-sandbox.sh:copy_file \"${FIXTURE_ROOT}/.opencode/agents/cp-improve-targetn\" \"${SANDBOX_DIR}/.opencode/agents/cp-improve-targetn\"\n","metadata":{"output":"=== CLUSTER 5: plugins/README.md entrypoint count ===\n2:title: \"OpenCode Plugin Entrypoints\"\n3:description: \"Six plugin entrypoint files OpenCode auto-loads at startup. Helper bridge modules live with their owning skills, not in this folder.\"\n6:# OpenCode Plugin Entrypoints\n8:OpenCode 1.3.17+ auto-loads JavaScript files in `.opencode/plugins/` at session start. This folder is intentionally limited to those entrypoint files so helper modules cannot be mistaken for plugins. Helpers and bridges live alongside their owning skills under `.opencode/skills/.../mcp_server/`.\n16:- [3. CURRENT ENTRYPOINTS](#3--current-entrypoints)\n36:1. Create the entrypoint here (`my-plugin.js`) with a **default export only** — no named exports (every named export is loaded as its own plugin; see Overview). Attach any test surface as a property on the default function.\n50:| `mk-deep-loop-guard.js` | Detection-layer `tool.execute.before` plugin for Task-tool dispatches targeting deep-loop sub-agents. Flags (default) or blocks (`MK_DEEP_LOOP_GUARD_REJECT=1`) a Deep Route header whose declared `mode` disagrees with `mode-registry.json`'s entry for the actual `subagent_type` being dispatched. Fails open on registry read errors. |\n63:This keeps plugin entrypoints minimal and lets owning skills own their bridge contracts.\n150:- `.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/hooks/` — sibling hook entrypoints (different runtime contract)\n\n=== CLUSTER 5b: actual plugins dir listing ===\n.opencode/plugins/mk-code-graph.js\n.opencode/plugins/mk-deep-loop-guard.js\n.opencode/plugins/mk-goal.js\n.opencode/plugins/mk-skill-advisor.js\n.opencode/plugins/mk-spec-memory.js\n.opencode/plugins/session-cleanup.js\n\n=== CLUSTER 4b: deep-improvement TOML references in docs ===\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/changelog/v1.5.0.0.md:- `.codex/agents/improve-agentn` → `.codex/agents/deep-improvementn`\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/changelog/v1.17.0.0.md:Every agent is authored once under `.opencode/agents/<name>.md` and mirrored to `.claude/agents/<name>.md` and `.codex/agents/<name>n` so each runtime ships the same behavior. Editing one copy without the others makes the runtimes silently disagree. A new `scripts/check-agent-mirror-sync.cjs` wraps the existing `verifyMirrorSync` library and turns it into a gate: given the changed agent files (or `--all`), it fails when any agent's mirrors drift from its `.opencode` canonical body — including a deleted mirror, or a deleted canonical whose runtime copies still linger. It is wired changed-files-scoped over added, modified, and deleted agent paths into `.opencode/hooks/pre-commit` and into a new `.github/workflows/agent-mirror-sync.yml` that fails closed if the checker is ever removed, so the divergence is caught at commit and pull-request time instead of in production. This promotes the mirror check from a deep-improvement promotion-only gate to an every-commit and every-PR gate.\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/changelog/v1.17.0.0.md:A gate that runs on every commit has to be precise, and the old normalizer was both too loose and too narrow. Each runtime mirror legitimately describes itself — a clause along the lines of \"this runtime's mirror; the canonical source lives in .opencode\" — and refers to its own runtime agent-file path (for example `.codex/agents/<name>n`), neither of which the canonical file carries. The old `normalizeRuntimeSpecificText` in `scripts/lib/mirror-sync-verify.cjs` counted the self-description clause as body drift and false-flagged healthy mirrors, while a blanket rule that collapsed every bare `.md`/`n` extension token was loose enough to mask a real format-extension mismatch. The normalizer now strips the self-description clause and normalizes only the runtime agent-file paths — so a mirror's reference to its own `.codex/agents/<name>n` no longer reads as drift — and the blanket bare-extension collapse is gone. The fix is deliberately conservative: it removes only the known self-description and agent-path shapes, and real body drift, including a genuine format-extension mismatch, is still caught.\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/changelog/v1.17.0.0.md:- `.codex/agents/contextn` — restored the dropped Tool-Inventory row to match the canonical agent body.\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/assets/agent_improvement/target_manifest.jsonc:      \".agents/commands/speckit/handovern\",\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/assets/agent_improvement/target_manifest.jsonc:      \".agents/commands/speckit/handovern\",\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/changelog/v1.0.1.0.md:| `.codex/agents/agent-improvern` | Modified | Mirror sync, wording fix |\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/scripts/shared/promote-candidate.cjs:    || /^(\\.\\/)?\\.opencode\\/agents\\/[^/]+\\n$/.test(normalized);\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/manual_testing_playbook/08--agent-discipline-stress-tests/setup-cp-sandbox.sh:require_path \"${FIXTURE_ROOT}/.opencode/agents/cp-improve-targetn\"\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/manual_testing_playbook/08--agent-discipline-stress-tests/setup-cp-sandbox.sh:copy_file \"${FIXTURE_ROOT}/.opencode/agents/cp-improve-targetn\" \"${SANDBOX_DIR}/.opencode/agents/cp-improve-targetn\"\n","exit":0,"truncated":false},"title":"echo \"=== CLUSTER 5: plugins/README.md entrypoint count ===\"\nrg -n -- \"[Ss]ix|[Tt]hree|[0-9]+ plugin|[Ee]ntrypoint|mk-deep-loop-guard\" .opencode/plugins/README.md 2>/dev/null\necho \"\"\necho \"=== CLUSTER 5b: actual plugins dir listing ===\"\nls -1 .opencode/plugins/*.js 2>/dev/null\necho \"\"\necho \"=== CLUSTER 4b: deep-improvement TOML references in docs ===\"\nrg -rn -- \"\\.toml\" .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/ 2>/dev/null | rg -iv \"node_modules\" | head -30 || echo \"(zero .toml hits in deep-improvement)\"","time":{"start":1782925209414,"end":1782925209416}},"id":"prt_f1e9faf23001tmna24HktLDTF4","sessionID":"ses_0e161eb7effeWxawnzJ6Yp6rgG","messageID":"msg_f1e9f5e4a001KB5tV9osq7A3VZ"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782925209437,"sessionID":"ses_0e161eb7effeWxawnzJ6Yp6rgG","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"call_39eee3f84e464c468450f23b","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"echo \"=== CLUSTER 1: --agent ai-council across cli-opencode ===\"\nrg -n -- \"ai-council\" .opencode/skills/cli-opencode/ 2>/dev/null | rg -i \"agent|--agent|direct|invoke|dispatch\" || echo \"(no ai-council+agent hits in cli-opencode)\"\necho \"\"\necho \"=== CLUSTER 1b: --agent ai-council literal across cli-opencode ===\"\nrg -n -- \"--agent ai-council\" .opencode/skills/cli-opencode/ 2>/dev/null || echo \"(zero --agent ai-council literal hits)\"\necho \"\"\necho \"=== CLUSTER 2/3/4: .opencode/agents/*.toml across deep-loop tree + cli-opencode ===\"\nrg -n -- \"\\.opencode/agents/\\*\\.toml\" .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/ .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/ .opencode/skills/cli-opencode/ 2>/dev/null || echo \"(zero .opencode/agents/*.toml hits in deep-loop+cli-opencode)\"\necho \"\"\necho \"=== CLUSTER 4: scan-integration.cjs MIRROR_TEMPLATES ===\"\nrg -n -- \"MIRROR_TEMPLATES|\\.toml\" .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/scripts/agent-improvement/scan-integration.cjs 2>/dev/null || echo \"(no hits)\"","workdir":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public"},"output":"=== CLUSTER 1: --agent ai-council across cli-opencode ===\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/SKILL.md:31:- **Agent dispatch** — task matches a specialized OpenCode agent. Primary agents (directly invokable via `--agent`): `general`, `plan` (built-in), `orchestrate`. Generic subagents fully dispatched via the orchestrate primary: `context`, `review`, `write`, `debug`, `ai-council`. Command-owned loop executors (`deep-research`, `deep-review`, `deep-improvement`, `prompt-improver`) are owned end-to-end by their parent `/deep:*` command; `orchestrate` may perform exactly one bounded hand-off dispatch to a recognized loop request, but never manages the loop itself. See §3 \"OpenCode Agent Delegation\" for the full contract.\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/SKILL.md:120:    \"AGENT_DISPATCH\":     {\"weight\": 4, \"keywords\": [\"delegate\", \"agent\", \"deep-research\", \"deep-review\", \"ai-council\", \"review agent\", \"context agent\"]},\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/SKILL.md:292:2. **`ai-council`** — dispatched either via its own `/deep:ai-council` command or via `orchestrate`'s registry-backed Task-dispatch. Direct `--agent ai-council` is rejected at the top level (`mode: subagent`); route through `/deep:ai-council` or `--agent orchestrate` with an ai-council-shaped prompt.\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/SKILL.md:295:Generic subagents (`context`, `review`, `write`, `debug`) and `ai-council` route through `orchestrate` for full Task-tool dispatch; loop executors (`deep-research`, `deep-review`, `deep-improvement`, `prompt-improver`) are loop-owned by their parent commands, with `orchestrate` limited to a single bounded hand-off when it recognizes one of these as the target.\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/assets/prompt_templates.md:372:**Agent:** `ai-council` (`mode: subagent` — dispatched via `orchestrate` or `/deep:ai-council`, never direct top-level `--agent ai-council`)\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/assets/prompt_templates.md:392:  \"Dispatch @ai-council: <prompt>\" 2>&1\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/README.md:76:You get structured JSON events streamed to stdout as the session runs, ending with a final tool-result message. The `</dev/null` is mandatory on non-interactive runs. Do not pass top-level `--agent` by default: `context`, `review`, `debug`, and `ai-council` are subagents that route through a primary/orchestrate path (or, for `ai-council`, through its own `/deep:ai-council` command), and direct top-level `--agent` use is only conditionally allowed for primary agents such as `plan` or `orchestrate` after `opencode run --help` confirms acceptance.\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/README.md:164:| `--agent general` fails or warns | The default/general path is selected by omitting `--agent` | Omit `--agent general`; use `orchestrate` only when it is the documented primary route and help-verified. Route `context`, `review`, `debug`, and `ai-council` through the documented primary/Task path (or, for `ai-council`, `/deep:ai-council`) instead of direct top-level `--agent` examples. |\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/references/agent_delegation.md:133:| `ai-council` | Multi-strategy planning architect | Complex planning that benefits from comparing multiple solution strategies. PLANNING-ONLY |\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/references/agent_delegation.md:186:### @ai-council — Multi-Strategy Planning Architect\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/references/agent_delegation.md:197:**Command-only (as of `mode: subagent`).** Direct `opencode run --agent ai-council` is no longer reachable — `ai-council.md` is `mode: subagent`, not directly selectable as a top-level session agent. Dispatch via `/deep:ai-council` for a full session, or via `opencode run --agent general \"...\"` and let `general`/`orchestrate`'s own routing Task-dispatch to `@ai-council` for a single planning pass.\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/references/agent_delegation.md:229:| Multi-strategy planning | `ai-council` | **Command-only.** Dispatch via `/deep:ai-council` for a full session, or `opencode run --agent general --variant high --format json --dir /repo \"Plan the authentication redesign — compare three strategies.\"` and let orchestrate's routing Task-dispatch `@ai-council`. Direct `opencode run --agent ai-council` is forbidden as of `mode: subagent`. |\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/references/agent_delegation.md:299:| `ai-council` | PLANNING-ONLY — no file modifications |\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/references/opencode_tools.md:139:The `--agent <slug>` flag loads an agent definition from `.opencode/agents/<slug>.md`. The frontmatter pins the model, tool permissions, and system prompt. Specialized agents (`deep-research`, `deep-review`, `context`, `review`, `ai-council`, etc.) provide domain-specific behavior the calling AI can target.\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/changelog/v1.1.0.0.md:15:cli-opencode previously documented 9 agents as `--agent`-invokable, but only 4 are actually primary (directly callable). The `general` and `plan` agents are OpenCode built-ins; `orchestrate` is mode=primary; `multi-ai-council` is mode=all. The other 8 (`context`, `debug`, `review`, `write`, `deep-research`, `deep-review`, `deep-agent-improvement`, `prompt-improver`) are mode=subagent and dispatch via Task tool from a primary. SKILL.md §3 now splits into two tables — primary agents (directly invokable) and subagents (routed via `--agent orchestrate \"Use the X subagent to ...\"`).\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/changelog/v1.1.0.0.md:23:Scenarios CO-014 (context), CO-015 (review), CO-016 (write), CO-032 (deep-research), CO-033 (deep-review) previously dispatched `--agent <subagent>` directly, which opencode rejects with a \"agent X is a subagent, not a primary agent. Falling back to default agent\" warning. Each scenario's TEST EXECUTION bash command now dispatches via `--agent orchestrate` with a `\"Use the <subagent> subagent to ...\"` prompt prefix. CO-013 (general), CO-017 (multi-ai-council), CO-034 (orchestrate) were already correctly using primaries.\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/manual_testing_playbook/04--agent-routing/multi-ai-council-multi-strategy.md:3:description: \"This scenario validates the ai-council planning-only agent for `CO-017`. It focuses on confirming `--agent orchestrate` dispatching `@ai-council` (mode: subagent) produces multiple distinct strategies scored across a rubric and respects the planning-only constraint (no file modifications).\"\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/manual_testing_playbook/04--agent-routing/multi-ai-council-multi-strategy.md:15:This scenario validates the Ultra-think multi-strategy planning agent for `CO-017`. It focuses on confirming `--agent orchestrate` dispatching `@ai-council` (`mode: subagent`) generates at least 3 distinct solution strategies, scores each across a multi-dimension rubric, recommends one with rationale, AND respects the planning-only constraint documented in `references/agent_delegation.md` §7 (no file modifications).\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/manual_testing_playbook/04--agent-routing/multi-ai-council-multi-strategy.md:19:`ai-council` is the canonical multi-strategy planning architect. Its value depends on two contracts: produce diverse, well-scored strategies (not a single linear plan). Never write files (planning-only LEAF constraint). If either contract breaks, the agent loses its differentiator from `general` and its safety story for use in pre-implementation planning. This test validates both contracts simultaneously.\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/manual_testing_playbook/04--agent-routing/multi-ai-council-multi-strategy.md:27:- Objective: Confirm `--agent orchestrate` dispatching `@ai-council` produces at least 3 distinct strategies scored on at least 3 dimensions with an explicit recommendation, AND no file modifications occur.\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/manual_testing_playbook/04--agent-routing/multi-ai-council-multi-strategy.md:28:- Real user request: `Use opencode run with --agent orchestrate to have @ai-council compare 3 strategies for migrating a small JS module from CommonJS to ESM. Confirm the response has 3 strategies, each scored on at least 3 dimensions, an explicit recommendation, AND no files were modified.`\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/manual_testing_playbook/04--agent-routing/multi-ai-council-multi-strategy.md:29:- RCAF Prompt: `As an external-AI conductor planning a CommonJS-to-ESM migration of a single hypothetical module, dispatch --agent orchestrate with a request for @ai-council to compare three strategies (big-bang rewrite, incremental wrapper, dual-build). Verify the response presents three distinct strategies, scores each across risk/effort/timeline/reversibility, recommends one with rationale, and does NOT modify any files in the repo. Return a concise pass/fail verdict naming the recommended strategy and the dimension count per strategy.`\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/manual_testing_playbook/04--agent-routing/multi-ai-council-multi-strategy.md:30:- Expected execution process: External-AI orchestrator snapshots a few sentinel file mtimes, dispatches with `--agent orchestrate` and a prompt requesting `@ai-council`, validates the response presents three distinct strategies with scoring across at least three dimensions and an explicit recommendation and confirms the sentinel mtimes are unchanged.\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/manual_testing_playbook/04--agent-routing/multi-ai-council-multi-strategy.md:43:3. Dispatch with `--agent orchestrate` and a prompt requesting `@ai-council` run the multi-strategy planning.\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/manual_testing_playbook/04--agent-routing/multi-ai-council-multi-strategy.md:51:| CO-017 | Ultra-think multi-strategy planning | Confirm `--agent orchestrate` dispatching `@ai-council` produces 3+ distinct strategies scored across 3+ dimensions with no file writes | `As an external-AI conductor planning a CommonJS-to-ESM migration of a single hypothetical module, dispatch --agent orchestrate with a request for @ai-council to compare three strategies (big-bang rewrite, incremental wrapper, dual-build). Verify the response presents three distinct strategies, scores each across risk/effort/timeline/reversibility, recommends one with rationale, and does NOT modify any files in the repo. Return a concise pass/fail verdict naming the recommended strategy and the dimension count per strategy.` | 1. `bash: stat -f '%m %N' .opencode/skills/cli-opencode/SKILL.md .opencode/skills/cli-opencode/references/cli_reference.md > /tmp/co-017-mtimes-before.txt && cat /tmp/co-017-mtimes-before.txt` -> 2. `bash: opencode run --model deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro --agent orchestrate --variant high --format json --dir \"$(pwd)\" \"Dispatch @ai-council: compare three strategies for migrating a single CommonJS Node module to ESM: (1) big-bang rewrite, (2) incremental wrapper, (3) dual-build. Score each across risk, effort, timeline, and reversibility. Recommend one with rationale. PLANNING-ONLY — do not modify any files.\" > /tmp/co-017-events.jsonl 2>&1` -> 3. `bash: echo \"Exit: $?\"` -> 4. `bash: stat -f '%m %N' .opencode/skills/cli-opencode/SKILL.md .opencode/skills/cli-opencode/references/cli_reference.md > /tmp/co-017-mtimes-after.txt && diff /tmp/co-017-mtimes-before.txt /tmp/co-017-mtimes-after.txt && echo SENTINEL_MTIMES_OK` -> 5. `bash: jq -r 'select(.type == \"tool.call\") \\| .payload.name' /tmp/co-017-events.jsonl \\| grep -ciE '(Edit\\|Write)'` -> 6. `bash: jq -r 'select(.type == \"message.delta\" or .type == \"session.completed\") \\| .payload' /tmp/co-017-events.jsonl \\| grep -ciE '(big-bang\\|incremental wrapper\\|dual-build)'` -> 7. `bash: jq -r 'select(.type == \"message.delta\" or .type == \"session.completed\") \\| .payload' /tmp/co-017-events.jsonl \\| grep -ciE '(risk\\|effort\\|timeline\\|reversibility)'` -> 8. `bash: jq -r 'select(.type == \"message.delta\" or .type == \"session.completed\") \\| .payload' /tmp/co-017-events.jsonl \\| grep -ciE '(recommend\\|prefer\\|choose)'` | Step 1: sentinel mtimes captured; Step 2: events captured; Step 3: exit 0; Step 4: SENTINEL_MTIMES_OK printed; Step 5: count of Edit/Write tool.calls = 0; Step 6: count of strategy mentions >= 3; Step 7: count of dimension mentions >= 4; Step 8: at least one explicit recommendation phrase | `/tmp/co-017-events.jsonl`, `/tmp/co-017-mtimes-{before,after}.txt`, terminal grep counts | PASS if exit 0 AND SENTINEL_MTIMES_OK AND zero Edit/Write tool.calls AND >= 3 strategies AND >= 4 dimensions AND explicit recommendation; FAIL if any check fails | 1. If a sentinel mtime changed, the planning-only contract is violated — file a P0 LEAF safety regression; 2. If only 1-2 strategies appear, the agent collapsed to a linear plan — re-prompt with stronger \"produce 3 distinct strategies\" wording; 3. If dimensions are missing, add explicit \"score each on risk/effort/timeline/reversibility\" instructions; 4. If `--agent ai-council` is rejected (subagent, not top-level), confirm the request is going through `--agent orchestrate` instead |\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/manual_testing_playbook/04--agent-routing/multi-ai-council-multi-strategy.md:55:For rubric depth, ask the agent to produce a 5x5 markdown table with strategies as rows and dimensions as columns. Confirm every cell has a non-empty score. This is the \"ideal output shape\" for ai-council dispatches and stresses the agent's ability to produce structured output.\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/manual_testing_playbook/04--agent-routing/multi-ai-council-multi-strategy.md:66:| `../../references/agent_delegation.md` (§3 ai-council property table + §7 LEAF constraints) | Ultra-think planning-only contract |\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/manual_testing_playbook/04--agent-routing/multi-ai-council-multi-strategy.md:72:| `../../SKILL.md` | §3 agent routing table (`ai-council` row) |\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/manual_testing_playbook/04--agent-routing/multi-ai-council-multi-strategy.md:73:| `../../assets/prompt_templates.md` (TEMPLATE 10: Multi-strategy planning via @MULTI-AI COUNCIL) | Canonical ai-council prompt shape |\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/manual_testing_playbook/04--agent-routing/multi-ai-council-multi-strategy.md:82:- Feature file path: `04--agent-routing/005-ai-council-multi-strategy.md`\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md:37:Coverage note (2026-04-26): Covers the canonical default invocation (`deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro` + `--variant high` + `--agent general` + `--format json`), the three documented use cases (external dispatch, parallel detached, cross-AI handback per ADR-002), the multi-provider matrix (deepseek direct API default with full variant range, kimi-for-coding direct plan), the 8-agent routing surface (general / context / orchestrate / write / review / debug / deep-research / deep-review / ai-council), session continuity surfaces (`-c`, `-s <id>`, `--fork`, `--share` gate), the 16-template inventory plus CLEAR quality card, the parallel-detached exception path with `</dev/null` worker farms, cross-repo dispatch via `--dir` and cross-server dispatch via `--attach`. Self-invocation refusal (ADR-001) is enforced upstream by the skill's layered detection guard and is exercised in CO-008 (refusal path) and CO-031 (cross-repo nested guard) respectively. Destructive scenarios are limited to operator-confirmed `--share` flows (CHK-033). The playbook never publishes share URLs without explicit operator approval.\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md:362:This category covers 8 scenario summaries while the linked feature files remain the canonical execution contract. cli-opencode distinguishes 4 primary agents (directly invokable via --agent: general + plan as OpenCode built-ins; orchestrate + ai-council as repo-defined primaries) from N subagents (context, review, write, debug, deep-research, deep-review, deep-improvement, prompt-improver) which dispatch as Task subagents from a primary. CO-013..CO-017 + CO-032..CO-034 exercise both surfaces — direct primary invocation and primary-dispatches-subagent routing.\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md:417:Verify `--agent orchestrate` dispatching `ai-council` (`mode: subagent`) produces at least 3 distinct solution strategies scored across at least 3 dimensions with an explicit recommendation, AND respects the planning-only constraint (no file modifications).\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md:421:Prompt summary: As an external-AI conductor planning a CommonJS-to-ESM migration of a single hypothetical module, dispatch `--agent orchestrate` with a prompt requesting `@ai-council` to compare three strategies (big-bang rewrite, incremental wrapper, dual-build). Verify the response presents three distinct strategies, scores each across risk/effort/timeline/reversibility, recommends one with rationale and does NOT modify any files in the repo.\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md:427:> **Feature File:** [CO-017](04--agent-routing/multi-ai-council-multi-strategy.md)\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md:469:Prompt summary: As an external-AI conductor facing a complex task that requires multiple OpenCode specializations in sequence, dispatch `opencode run --agent orchestrate --variant high --format json --dir <repo-root>` and ask for a decomposition naming at least 3 specialist agents (for example context, review, write, ai-council) and explicit handoffs. Verify the response names at least 3 distinct agent slugs in sequence with handoffs and that zero nested opencode-run tool.calls appear. Return a verdict naming the agents in planned order and confirming the no-nested-run constraint.\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md:827:- CO-017: [Ultra-think multi-strategy planning](04--agent-routing/multi-ai-council-multi-strategy.md)\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/manual_testing_playbook/04--agent-routing/orchestrate-agent-multi-agent.md:29:- RCAF Prompt: `As an external-AI conductor facing a complex task that requires multiple OpenCode specializations in sequence, dispatch opencode run --agent orchestrate --variant high --format json --dir <repo-root> \"Plan a comprehensive audit of the cli-opencode skill itself. Decompose into a sequence of OpenCode specialist agents (e.g., context, review, write, ai-council) with explicit handoffs between steps. Name each agent slug, the artifact each step produces, and what it hands to the next step. Do not dispatch nested opencode run invocations.\" Verify the response names at least 3 distinct agent slugs in sequence with handoffs and that zero nested opencode-run tool.calls appear. Return a verdict naming the agents in planned order and confirming the no-nested-run constraint.`\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/manual_testing_playbook/04--agent-routing/orchestrate-agent-multi-agent.md:31:- Expected signals: Dispatch exits 0. JSON event stream contains session.started, message.delta events and session.completed. Response or summary names at least 3 distinct agent slugs from the documented roster (general, context, review, write, debug, deep-research, deep-review, ai-council, deep-improvement). Steps are sequenced (Step 1, Step 2, etc.) with handoff descriptions. Zero `opencode run` nested invocations in tool.call payloads. Dispatched command line includes `--agent orchestrate`.\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/manual_testing_playbook/04--agent-routing/orchestrate-agent-multi-agent.md:50:| CO-034 | Orchestrate agent multi-agent coordination | Verify --agent orchestrate produces a sequenced multi-agent plan with no nested opencode run dispatches | `As an external-AI conductor facing a complex task that requires multiple OpenCode specializations in sequence, dispatch opencode run --agent orchestrate --variant high --format json --dir <repo-root> \"Plan a comprehensive audit of the cli-opencode skill itself. Decompose into a sequence of OpenCode specialist agents (e.g., context, review, write, ai-council) with explicit handoffs between steps. Name each agent slug, the artifact each step produces, and what it hands to the next step. Do not dispatch nested opencode run invocations.\" Verify the response names at least 3 distinct agent slugs in sequence with handoffs and that zero nested opencode-run tool.calls appear. Return a verdict naming the agents in planned order and confirming the no-nested-run constraint.` | 1. `bash: rm -rf /tmp/co-034-events.jsonl && git status --porcelain > /tmp/co-034-pre.txt` -> 2. `opencode run --model deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro --agent orchestrate --variant high --format json --dir \"$(pwd)\" \"Plan a comprehensive audit of the cli-opencode skill itself. Decompose into a sequence of OpenCode specialist agents (for example context, review, write, ai-council) with explicit handoffs between steps. Name each agent slug, the artifact each step produces, and what it hands to the next step. Do not dispatch nested opencode run invocations.\" > /tmp/co-034-events.jsonl 2>&1` -> 3. `bash: echo \"Exit: $?\"` -> 4. `bash: jq -r 'select(.type == \"session.completed\") \\| .payload.summary // empty' /tmp/co-034-events.jsonl > /tmp/co-034-summary.txt` -> 5. `bash: grep -ciE '(general\\|context\\|review\\|write\\|debug\\|deep-research\\|deep-review\\|ai-council\\|deep-improvement)' /tmp/co-034-summary.txt` -> 6. `bash: grep -ciE '(step [0-9]+\\|handoff\\|hand off\\|hands to\\|passes to)' /tmp/co-034-summary.txt` -> 7. `bash: jq -r 'select(.type == \"tool.call\") \\| .payload.input.command // empty' /tmp/co-034-events.jsonl \\| grep -ciE 'opencode run' \\| tr -d ' '` -> 8. `bash: git status --porcelain > /tmp/co-034-post.txt && diff /tmp/co-034-pre.txt /tmp/co-034-post.txt && echo OK_TREE_CLEAN` | Step 1: pre-snapshot captured; Step 2: dispatch captured; Step 3: exit 0; Step 4: session.completed summary extracted; Step 5: distinct agent-slug count >= 3 (across multiple grep hits); Step 6: handoff or step keyword count >= 2; Step 7: nested `opencode run` count = 0; Step 8: `OK_TREE_CLEAN` printed | `/tmp/co-034-events.jsonl`, `/tmp/co-034-summary.txt`, pre and post tree-status diff | PASS if exit 0 AND >= 3 distinct agent slugs AND handoffs described AND nested opencode-run count = 0 AND working tree clean AND `--agent orchestrate` in dispatch; FAIL if any check misses or nested runs appear | (1) If nested `opencode run` count > 0, the orchestrator violated the no-nested-run constraint, file a high-severity bug per agent_delegation.md §6; (2) if fewer than 3 slugs are named, refine the prompt to require explicit decomposition into at least 3 specialists; (3) if `--agent orchestrate` is rejected, run `opencode agent list` to confirm the agent is registered |\n\n=== CLUSTER 1b: --agent ai-council literal across cli-opencode ===\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/assets/prompt_templates.md:372:**Agent:** `ai-council` (`mode: subagent` — dispatched via `orchestrate` or `/deep:ai-council`, never direct top-level `--agent ai-council`)\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/SKILL.md:292:2. **`ai-council`** — dispatched either via its own `/deep:ai-council` command or via `orchestrate`'s registry-backed Task-dispatch. Direct `--agent ai-council` is rejected at the top level (`mode: subagent`); route through `/deep:ai-council` or `--agent orchestrate` with an ai-council-shaped prompt.\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/manual_testing_playbook/04--agent-routing/multi-ai-council-multi-strategy.md:51:| CO-017 | Ultra-think multi-strategy planning | Confirm `--agent orchestrate` dispatching `@ai-council` produces 3+ distinct strategies scored across 3+ dimensions with no file writes | `As an external-AI conductor planning a CommonJS-to-ESM migration of a single hypothetical module, dispatch --agent orchestrate with a request for @ai-council to compare three strategies (big-bang rewrite, incremental wrapper, dual-build). Verify the response presents three distinct strategies, scores each across risk/effort/timeline/reversibility, recommends one with rationale, and does NOT modify any files in the repo. Return a concise pass/fail verdict naming the recommended strategy and the dimension count per strategy.` | 1. `bash: stat -f '%m %N' .opencode/skills/cli-opencode/SKILL.md .opencode/skills/cli-opencode/references/cli_reference.md > /tmp/co-017-mtimes-before.txt && cat /tmp/co-017-mtimes-before.txt` -> 2. `bash: opencode run --model deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro --agent orchestrate --variant high --format json --dir \"$(pwd)\" \"Dispatch @ai-council: compare three strategies for migrating a single CommonJS Node module to ESM: (1) big-bang rewrite, (2) incremental wrapper, (3) dual-build. Score each across risk, effort, timeline, and reversibility. Recommend one with rationale. PLANNING-ONLY — do not modify any files.\" > /tmp/co-017-events.jsonl 2>&1` -> 3. `bash: echo \"Exit: $?\"` -> 4. `bash: stat -f '%m %N' .opencode/skills/cli-opencode/SKILL.md .opencode/skills/cli-opencode/references/cli_reference.md > /tmp/co-017-mtimes-after.txt && diff /tmp/co-017-mtimes-before.txt /tmp/co-017-mtimes-after.txt && echo SENTINEL_MTIMES_OK` -> 5. `bash: jq -r 'select(.type == \"tool.call\") \\| .payload.name' /tmp/co-017-events.jsonl \\| grep -ciE '(Edit\\|Write)'` -> 6. `bash: jq -r 'select(.type == \"message.delta\" or .type == \"session.completed\") \\| .payload' /tmp/co-017-events.jsonl \\| grep -ciE '(big-bang\\|incremental wrapper\\|dual-build)'` -> 7. `bash: jq -r 'select(.type == \"message.delta\" or .type == \"session.completed\") \\| .payload' /tmp/co-017-events.jsonl \\| grep -ciE '(risk\\|effort\\|timeline\\|reversibility)'` -> 8. `bash: jq -r 'select(.type == \"message.delta\" or .type == \"session.completed\") \\| .payload' /tmp/co-017-events.jsonl \\| grep -ciE '(recommend\\|prefer\\|choose)'` | Step 1: sentinel mtimes captured; Step 2: events captured; Step 3: exit 0; Step 4: SENTINEL_MTIMES_OK printed; Step 5: count of Edit/Write tool.calls = 0; Step 6: count of strategy mentions >= 3; Step 7: count of dimension mentions >= 4; Step 8: at least one explicit recommendation phrase | `/tmp/co-017-events.jsonl`, `/tmp/co-017-mtimes-{before,after}.txt`, terminal grep counts | PASS if exit 0 AND SENTINEL_MTIMES_OK AND zero Edit/Write tool.calls AND >= 3 strategies AND >= 4 dimensions AND explicit recommendation; FAIL if any check fails | 1. If a sentinel mtime changed, the planning-only contract is violated — file a P0 LEAF safety regression; 2. If only 1-2 strategies appear, the agent collapsed to a linear plan — re-prompt with stronger \"produce 3 distinct strategies\" wording; 3. If dimensions are missing, add explicit \"score each on risk/effort/timeline/reversibility\" instructions; 4. If `--agent ai-council` is rejected (subagent, not top-level), confirm the request is going through `--agent orchestrate` instead |\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/references/agent_delegation.md:197:**Command-only (as of `mode: subagent`).** Direct `opencode run --agent ai-council` is no longer reachable — `ai-council.md` is `mode: subagent`, not directly selectable as a top-level session agent. Dispatch via `/deep:ai-council` for a full session, or via `opencode run --agent general \"...\"` and let `general`/`orchestrate`'s own routing Task-dispatch to `@ai-council` for a single planning pass.\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/references/agent_delegation.md:229:| Multi-strategy planning | `ai-council` | **Command-only.** Dispatch via `/deep:ai-council` for a full session, or `opencode run --agent general --variant high --format json --dir /repo \"Plan the authentication redesign — compare three strategies.\"` and let orchestrate's routing Task-dispatch `@ai-council`. Direct `opencode run --agent ai-council` is forbidden as of `mode: subagent`. |\n\n=== CLUSTER 2/3/4: .opencode/agents/*.toml across deep-loop tree + cli-opencode ===\n(zero .opencode/agents/*.toml hits in deep-loop+cli-opencode)\n\n=== CLUSTER 4: scan-integration.cjs MIRROR_TEMPLATES ===\n15:const MIRROR_TEMPLATES = [\n102:  return MIRROR_TEMPLATES.map((tpl) => {\n","metadata":{"output":"=== CLUSTER 1: --agent ai-council across cli-opencode ===\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/SKILL.md:31:- **Agent dispatch** — task matches a specialized OpenCode agent. Primary agents (directly invokable via `--agent`): `general`, `plan` (built-in), `orchestrate`. Generic subagents fully dispatched via the orchestrate primary: `context`, `review`, `write`, `debug`, `ai-council`. Command-owned loop executors (`deep-research`, `deep-review`, `deep-improvement`, `prompt-improver`) are owned end-to-end by their parent `/deep:*` command; `orchestrate` may perform exactly one bounded hand-off dispatch to a recognized loop request, but never manages the loop itself. See §3 \"OpenCode Agent Delegation\" for the full contract.\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/SKILL.md:120:    \"AGENT_DISPATCH\":     {\"weight\": 4, \"keywords\": [\"delegate\", \"agent\", \"deep-research\", \"deep-review\", \"ai-council\", \"review agent\", \"context agent\"]},\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/SKILL.md:292:2. **`ai-council`** — dispatched either via its own `/deep:ai-council` command or via `orchestrate`'s registry-backed Task-dispatch. Direct `--agent ai-council` is rejected at the top level (`mode: subagent`); route through `/deep:ai-council` or `--agent orchestrate` with an ai-council-shaped prompt.\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/SKILL.md:295:Generic subagents (`context`, `review`, `write`, `debug`) and `ai-council` route through `orchestrate` for full Task-tool dispatch; loop executors (`deep-research`, `deep-review`, `deep-improvement`, `prompt-improver`) are loop-owned by their parent commands, with `orchestrate` limited to a single bounded hand-off when it recognizes one of these as the target.\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/assets/prompt_templates.md:372:**Agent:** `ai-council` (`mode: subagent` — dispatched via `orchestrate` or `/deep:ai-council`, never direct top-level `--agent ai-council`)\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/assets/prompt_templates.md:392:  \"Dispatch @ai-council: <prompt>\" 2>&1\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/README.md:76:You get structured JSON events streamed to stdout as the session runs, ending with a final tool-result message. The `</dev/null` is mandatory on non-interactive runs. Do not pass top-level `--agent` by default: `context`, `review`, `debug`, and `ai-council` are subagents that route through a primary/orchestrate path (or, for `ai-council`, through its own `/deep:ai-council` command), and direct top-level `--agent` use is only conditionally allowed for primary agents such as `plan` or `orchestrate` after `opencode run --help` confirms acceptance.\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/README.md:164:| `--agent general` fails or warns | The default/general path is selected by omitting `--agent` | Omit `--agent general`; use `orchestrate` only when it is the documented primary route and help-verified. Route `context`, `review`, `debug`, and `ai-council` through the documented primary/Task path (or, for `ai-council`, `/deep:ai-council`) instead of direct top-level `--agent` examples. |\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/references/agent_delegation.md:133:| `ai-council` | Multi-strategy planning architect | Complex planning that benefits from comparing multiple solution strategies. PLANNING-ONLY |\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/references/agent_delegation.md:186:### @ai-council — Multi-Strategy Planning Architect\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/references/agent_delegation.md:197:**Command-only (as of `mode: subagent`).** Direct `opencode run --agent ai-council` is no longer reachable — `ai-council.md` is `mode: subagent`, not directly selectable as a top-level session agent. Dispatch via `/deep:ai-council` for a full session, or via `opencode run --agent general \"...\"` and let `general`/`orchestrate`'s own routing Task-dispatch to `@ai-council` for a single planning pass.\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/references/agent_delegation.md:229:| Multi-strategy planning | `ai-council` | **Command-only.** Dispatch via `/deep:ai-council` for a full session, or `opencode run --agent general --variant high --format json --dir /repo \"Plan the authentication redesign — compare three strategies.\"` and let orchestrate's routing Task-dispatch `@ai-council`. Direct `opencode run --agent ai-council` is forbidden as of `mode: subagent`. |\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/references/agent_delegation.md:299:| `ai-council` | PLANNING-ONLY — no file modifications |\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/references/opencode_tools.md:139:The `--agent <slug>` flag loads an agent definition from `.opencode/agents/<slug>.md`. The frontmatter pins the model, tool permissions, and system prompt. Specialized agents (`deep-research`, `deep-review`, `context`, `review`, `ai-council`, etc.) provide domain-specific behavior the calling AI can target.\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/changelog/v1.1.0.0.md:15:cli-opencode previously documented 9 agents as `--agent`-invokable, but only 4 are actually primary (directly callable). The `general` and `plan` agents are OpenCode built-ins; `orchestrate` is mode=primary; `multi-ai-council` is mode=all. The other 8 (`context`, `debug`, `review`, `write`, `deep-research`, `deep-review`, `deep-agent-improvement`, `prompt-improver`) are mode=subagent and dispatch via Task tool from a primary. SKILL.md §3 now splits into two tables — primary agents (directly invokable) and subagents (routed via `--agent orchestrate \"Use the X subagent to ...\"`).\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/changelog/v1.1.0.0.md:23:Scenarios CO-014 (context), CO-015 (review), CO-016 (write), CO-032 (deep-research), CO-033 (deep-review) previously dispatched `--agent <subagent>` directly, which opencode rejects with a \"agent X is a subagent, not a primary agent. Falling back to default agent\" warning. Each scenario's TEST EXECUTION bash command now dispatches via `--agent orchestrate` with a `\"Use the <subagent> subagent to ...\"` prompt prefix. CO-013 (general), CO-017 (multi-ai-council), CO-034 (orchestrate) were already correctly using primaries.\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/manual_testing_playbook/04--agent-routing/multi-ai-council-multi-strategy.md:3:description: \"This scenario validates the ai-council planning-only agent for `CO-017`. It focuses on confirming `--agent orchestrate` dispatching `@ai-council` (mode: subagent) produces multiple distinct strategies scored across a rubric and respects the planning-only constraint (no file modifications).\"\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/manual_testing_playbook/04--agent-routing/multi-ai-council-multi-strategy.md:15:This scenario validates the Ultra-think multi-strategy planning agent for `CO-017`. It focuses on confirming `--agent orchestrate` dispatching `@ai-council` (`mode: subagent`) generates at least 3 distinct solution strategies, scores each across a multi-dimension rubric, recommends one with rationale, AND respects the planning-only constraint documented in `references/agent_delegation.md` §7 (no file modifications).\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/manual_testing_playbook/04--agent-routing/multi-ai-council-multi-strategy.md:19:`ai-council` is the canonical multi-strategy planning architect. Its value depends on two contracts: produce diverse, well-scored strategies (not a single linear plan). Never write files (planning-only LEAF constraint). If either contract breaks, the agent loses its differentiator from `general` and its safety story for use in pre-implementation planning. This test validates both contracts simultaneously.\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/manual_testing_playbook/04--agent-routing/multi-ai-council-multi-strategy.md:27:- Objective: Confirm `--agent orchestrate` dispatching `@ai-council` produces at least 3 distinct strategies scored on at least 3 dimensions with an explicit recommendation, AND no file modifications occur.\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/manual_testing_playbook/04--agent-routing/multi-ai-council-multi-strategy.md:28:- Real user request: `Use opencode run with --agent orchestrate to have @ai-council compare 3 strategies for migrating a small JS module from CommonJS to ESM. Confirm the response has 3 strategies, each scored on at least 3 dimensions, an explicit recommendation, AND no files were modified.`\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/manual_testing_playbook/04--agent-routing/multi-ai-council-multi-strategy.md:29:- RCAF Prompt: `As an external-AI conductor planning a CommonJS-to-ESM migration of a single hypothetical module, dispatch --agent orchestrate with a request for @ai-council to compare three strategies (big-bang rewrite, incremental wrapper, dual-build). Verify the response presents three distinct strategies, scores each across risk/effort/timeline/reversibility, recommends one with rationale, and does NOT modify any files in the repo. Return a concise pass/fail verdict naming the recommended strategy and the dimension count per strategy.`\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/manual_testing_playbook/04--agent-routing/multi-ai-council-multi-strategy.md:30:- Expected execution process: External-AI orchestrator snapshots a few sentinel file mtimes, dispatches with `--agent orchestrate` and a prompt requesting `@ai-council`, validates the response presents three distinct strategies with scoring across at least three dimensions and an explicit recommendation and confirms the sentinel mtimes are unchanged.\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/manual_testing_playbook/04--agent-routing/multi-ai-council-multi-strategy.md:43:3. Dispatch with `--agent orchestrate` and a prompt requesting `@ai-council` run the multi-strategy planning.\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/manual_testing_playbook/04--agent-routing/multi-ai-council-multi-strategy.md:51:| CO-017 | Ultra-think multi-strategy planning | Confirm `--agent orchestrate` dispatching `@ai-council` produces 3+ distinct strategies scored across 3+ dimensions with no file writes | `As an external-AI conductor planning a CommonJS-to-ESM migration of a single hypothetical module, dispatch --agent orchestrate with a request for @ai-council to compare three strategies (big-bang rewrite, incremental wrapper, dual-build). Verify the response presents three distinct strategies, scores each across risk/effort/timeline/reversibility, recommends one with rationale, and does NOT modify any files in the repo. Return a concise pass/fail verdict naming the recommended strategy and the dimension count per strategy.` | 1. `bash: stat -f '%m %N' .opencode/skills/cli-opencode/SKILL.md .opencode/skills/cli-opencode/references/cli_reference.md > /tmp/co-017-mtimes-before.txt && cat /tmp/co-017-mtimes-before.txt` -> 2. `bash: opencode run --model deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro --agent orchestrate --variant high --format json --dir \"$(pwd)\" \"Dispatch @ai-council: compare three strategies for migrating a single CommonJS Node module to ESM: (1) big-bang rewrite, (2) incremental wrapper, (3) dual-build. Score each across risk, effort, timeline, and reversibility. Recommend one with rationale. PLANNING-ONLY — do not modify any files.\" > /tmp/co-017-events.jsonl 2>&1` -> 3. `bash: echo \"Exit: $?\"` -> 4. `bash: stat -f '%m %N' .opencode/skills/cli-opencode/SKILL.md .opencode/skills/cli-opencode/references/cli_reference.md > /tmp/co-017-mtimes-after.txt && diff /tmp/co-017-mtimes-before.txt /tmp/co-017-mtimes-after.txt && echo SENTINEL_MTIMES_OK` -> 5. `bash: jq -r 'select(.type == \"tool.call\") \\| .payload.name' /tmp/co-017-events.jsonl \\| grep -ciE '(Edit\\|Write)'` -> 6. `bash: jq -r 'select(.type == \"message.delta\" or .type == \"session.completed\") \\| .payload' /tmp/co-017-events.jsonl \\| grep -ciE '(big-bang\\|incremental wrapper\\|dual-build)'` -> 7. `bash: jq -r 'select(.type == \"message.delta\" or .type == \"session.completed\") \\| .payload' /tmp/co-017-events.jsonl \\| grep -ciE '(risk\\|effort\\|timeline\\|reversibility)'` -> 8. `bash: jq -r 'select(.type == \"message.delta\" or .type == \"session.completed\") \\| .payload' /tmp/co-017-events.jsonl \\| grep -ciE '(recommend\\|prefer\\|choose)'` | Step 1: sentinel mtimes captured; Step 2: events captured; Step 3: exit 0; Step 4: SENTINEL_MTIMES_OK printed; Step 5: count of Edit/Write tool.calls = 0; Step 6: count of strategy mentions >= 3; Step 7: count of dimension mentions >= 4; Step 8: at least one explicit recommendation phrase | `/tmp/co-017-events.jsonl`, `/tmp/co-017-mtimes-{before,after}.txt`, terminal grep counts | PASS if exit 0 AND SENTINEL_MTIMES_OK AND zero Edit/Write tool.calls AND >= 3 strategies AND >= 4 dimensions AND explicit recommendation; FAIL if any check fails | 1. If a sentinel mtime changed, the planning-only contract is violated — file a P0 LEAF safety regression; 2. If only 1-2 strategies appear, the agent collapsed to a linear plan — re-prompt with stronger \"produce 3 distinct strategies\" wording; 3. If dimensions are missing, add explicit \"score each on risk/effort/timeline/reversibility\" instructions; 4. If `--agent ai-council` is rejected (subagent, not top-level), confirm the request is going through `--agent orchestrate` instead |\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/manual_testing_playbook/04--agent-routing/multi-ai-council-multi-strategy.md:55:For rubric depth, ask the agent to produce a 5x5 markdown table with strategies as rows and dimensions as columns. Confirm every cell has a non-empty score. This is the \"ideal output shape\" for ai-council dispatches and stresses the agent's ability to produce structured output.\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/manual_testing_playbook/04--agent-routing/multi-ai-council-multi-strategy.md:66:| `../../references/agent_delegation.md` (§3 ai-council property table + §7 LEAF constraints) | Ultra-think planning-only contract |\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/manual_testing_playbook/04--agent-routing/multi-ai-council-multi-strategy.md:72:| `../../SKILL.md` | §3 agent routing table (`ai-council` row) |\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/manual_testing_playbook/04--agent-routing/multi-ai-council-multi-strategy.md:73:| `../../assets/prompt_templates.md` (TEMPLATE 10: Multi-strategy planning via @MULTI-AI COUNCIL) | Canonical ai-council prompt shape |\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/manual_testing_playbook/04--agent-routing/multi-ai-council-multi-strategy.md:82:- Feature file path: `04--agent-routing/005-ai-council-multi-strategy.md`\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md:37:Coverage note (2026-04-26): Covers the canonical default invocation (`deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro` + `--variant high` + `--agent general` + `--format json`), the three documented use cases (external dispatch, parallel detached, cross-AI handback per ADR-002), the multi-provider matrix (deepseek direct API default with full variant range, kimi-for-coding direct plan), the 8-agent routing surface (general / context / orchestrate / write / review / debug / deep-research / deep-review / ai-council), session continuity surfaces (`-c`, `-s <id>`, `--fork`, `--share` gate), the 16-template inventory plus CLEAR quality card, the parallel-detached exception path with `</dev/null` worker farms, cross-repo dispatch via `--dir` and cross-server dispatch via `--attach`. Self-invocation refusal (ADR-001) is enforced upstream by the skill's layered detection guard and is exercised in CO-008 (refusal path) and CO-031 (cross-repo nested guard) respectively. Destructive scenarios are limited to operator-confirmed `--share` flows (CHK-033). The playbook never publishes share URLs without explicit operator approval.\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md:362:This category covers 8 scenario summaries while the linked feature files remain the canonical execution contract. cli-opencode distinguishes 4 primary agents (directly invokable via --agent: general + plan as OpenCode built-ins; orchestrate + ai-council as repo-defined primaries) from N subagents (context, review, write, debug, deep-research, deep-review, deep-improvement, prompt-improver) which dispatch as Task subagents from a primary. CO-013..CO-017 + CO-032..CO-034 exercise both surfaces — direct primary invocation and primary-dispatches-subagent routing.\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md:417:Verify `--agent orchestrate` dispatching `ai-council` (`mode: subagent`) produces at least 3 distinct solution strategies scored across at least 3 dimensions with an explicit recommendation, AND respects the planning-only constraint (no file modifications).\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md:421:Prompt summary: As an external-AI conductor planning a CommonJS-to-ESM migration of a single hypothetical module, dispatch `--agent orchestrate` with a prompt requesting `@ai-council` to compare three strategies (big-bang rewrite, incremental wrapper, dual-build). Verify the response presents three distinct strategies, scores each across risk/effort/timeline/reversibility, recommends one with rationale and does NOT modify any files in the repo.\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md:427:> **Feature File:** [CO-017](04--agent-routing/multi-ai-council-multi-strategy.md)\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md:469:Prompt summary: As an external-AI conductor facing a complex task that requires multiple OpenCode specializations in sequence, dispatch `opencode run --agent orchestrate --variant high --format json --dir <repo-root>` and ask for a decomposition naming at least 3 specialist agents (for example context, review, write, ai-council) and explicit handoffs. Verify the response names at least 3 distinct agent slugs in sequence with handoffs and that zero nested opencode-run tool.calls appear. Return a verdict naming the agents in planned order and confirming the no-nested-run constraint.\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md:827:- CO-017: [Ultra-think multi-strategy planning](04--agent-routing/multi-ai-council-multi-strategy.md)\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/manual_testing_playbook/04--agent-routing/orchestrate-agent-multi-agent.md:29:- RCAF Prompt: `As an external-AI conductor facing a complex task that requires multiple OpenCode specializations in sequence, dispatch opencode run --agent orchestrate --variant high --format json --dir <repo-root> \"Plan a comprehensive audit of the cli-opencode skill itself. Decompose into a sequence of OpenCode specialist agents (e.g., context, review, write, ai-council) with explicit handoffs between steps. Name each agent slug, the artifact each step produces, and what it hands to the next step. Do not dispatch nested opencode run invocations.\" Verify the response names at least 3 distinct agent slugs in sequence with handoffs and that zero nested opencode-run tool.calls appear. Return a verdict naming the agents in planned order and confirming the no-nested-run constraint.`\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/manual_testing_playbook/04--agent-routing/orchestrate-agent-multi-agent.md:31:- Expected signals: Dispatch exits 0. JSON event stream contains session.started, message.delta events and session.completed. Response or summary names at least 3 distinct agent slugs from the documented roster (general, context, review, write, debug, deep-research, deep-review, ai-council, deep-improvement). Steps are sequenced (Step 1, Step 2, etc.) with handoff descriptions. Zero `opencode run` nested invocations in tool.call payloads. Dispatched command line includes `--agent orchestrate`.\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/manual_testing_playbook/04--agent-routing/orchestrate-agent-multi-agent.md:50:| CO-034 | Orchestrate agent multi-agent coordination | Verify --agent orchestrate produces a sequenced multi-agent plan with no nested opencode run dispatches | `As an external-AI conductor facing a complex task that requires multiple OpenCode specializations in sequence, dispatch opencode run --agent orchestrate --variant high --format json --dir <repo-root> \"Plan a comprehensive audit of the cli-opencode skill itself. Decompose into a sequence of OpenCode specialist agents (e.g., context, review, write, ai-council) with explicit handoffs between steps. Name each agent slug, the artifact each step produces, and what it hands to the next step. Do not dispatch nested opencode run invocations.\" Verify the response names at least 3 distinct agent slugs in sequence with handoffs and that zero nested opencode-run tool.calls appear. Return a verdict naming the agents in planned order and confirming the no-nested-run constraint.` | 1. `bash: rm -rf /tmp/co-034-events.jsonl && git status --porcelain > /tmp/co-034-pre.txt` -> 2. `opencode run --model deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro --agent orchestrate --variant high --format json --dir \"$(pwd)\" \"Plan a comprehensive audit of the cli-opencode skill itself. Decompose into a sequence of OpenCode specialist agents (for example context, review, write, ai-council) with explicit handoffs between steps. Name each agent slug, the artifact each step produces, and what it hands to the next step. Do not dispatch nested opencode run invocations.\" > /tmp/co-034-events.jsonl 2>&1` -> 3. `bash: echo \"Exit: $?\"` -> 4. `bash: jq -r 'select(.type == \"session.completed\") \\| .payload.summary // empty' /tmp/co-034-events.jsonl > /tmp/co-034-summary.txt` -> 5. `bash: grep -ciE '(general\\|context\\|review\\|write\\|debug\\|deep-research\\|deep-review\\|ai-council\\|deep-improvement)' /tmp/co-034-summary.txt` -> 6. `bash: grep -ciE '(step [0-9]+\\|handoff\\|hand off\\|hands to\\|passes to)' /tmp/co-034-summary.txt` -> 7. `bash: jq -r 'select(.type == \"tool.call\") \\| .payload.input.command // empty' /tmp/co-034-events.jsonl \\| grep -ciE 'opencode run' \\| tr -d ' '` -> 8. `bash: git status --porcelain > /tmp/co-034-post.txt && diff /tmp/co-034-pre.txt /tmp/co-034-post.txt && echo OK_TREE_CLEAN` | Step 1: pre-snapshot captured; Step 2: dispatch captured; Step 3: exit 0; Step 4: session.completed summary extracted; Step 5: distinct agent-slug count >= 3 (across multiple grep hits); Step 6: handoff or step keyword count >= 2; Step 7: nested `opencode run` count = 0; Step 8: `OK_TREE_CLEAN` printed | `/tmp/co-034-events.jsonl`, `/tmp/co-034-summary.txt`, pre and post tree-status diff | PASS if exit 0 AND >= 3 distinct agent slugs AND handoffs described AND nested opencode-run count = 0 AND working tree clean AND `--agent orchestrate` in dispatch; FAIL if any check misses or nested runs appear | (1) If nested `opencode run` count > 0, the orchestrator violated the no-nested-run constraint, file a high-severity bug per agent_delegation.md §6; (2) if fewer than 3 slugs are named, refine the prompt to require explicit decomposition into at least 3 specialists; (3) if `--agent orchestrate` is rejected, run `opencode agent list` to confirm the agent is registered |\n\n=== CLUSTER 1b: --agent ai-council literal across cli-opencode ===\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/assets/prompt_templates.md:372:**Agent:** `ai-council` (`mode: subagent` — dispatched via `orchestrate` or `/deep:ai-council`, never direct top-level `--agent ai-council`)\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/SKILL.md:292:2. **`ai-council`** — dispatched either via its own `/deep:ai-council` command or via `orchestrate`'s registry-backed Task-dispatch. Direct `--agent ai-council` is rejected at the top level (`mode: subagent`); route through `/deep:ai-council` or `--agent orchestrate` with an ai-council-shaped prompt.\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/manual_testing_playbook/04--agent-routing/multi-ai-council-multi-strategy.md:51:| CO-017 | Ultra-think multi-strategy planning | Confirm `--agent orchestrate` dispatching `@ai-council` produces 3+ distinct strategies scored across 3+ dimensions with no file writes | `As an external-AI conductor planning a CommonJS-to-ESM migration of a single hypothetical module, dispatch --agent orchestrate with a request for @ai-council to compare three strategies (big-bang rewrite, incremental wrapper, dual-build). Verify the response presents three distinct strategies, scores each across risk/effort/timeline/reversibility, recommends one with rationale, and does NOT modify any files in the repo. Return a concise pass/fail verdict naming the recommended strategy and the dimension count per strategy.` | 1. `bash: stat -f '%m %N' .opencode/skills/cli-opencode/SKILL.md .opencode/skills/cli-opencode/references/cli_reference.md > /tmp/co-017-mtimes-before.txt && cat /tmp/co-017-mtimes-before.txt` -> 2. `bash: opencode run --model deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro --agent orchestrate --variant high --format json --dir \"$(pwd)\" \"Dispatch @ai-council: compare three strategies for migrating a single CommonJS Node module to ESM: (1) big-bang rewrite, (2) incremental wrapper, (3) dual-build. Score each across risk, effort, timeline, and reversibility. Recommend one with rationale. PLANNING-ONLY — do not modify any files.\" > /tmp/co-017-events.jsonl 2>&1` -> 3. `bash: echo \"Exit: $?\"` -> 4. `bash: stat -f '%m %N' .opencode/skills/cli-opencode/SKILL.md .opencode/skills/cli-opencode/references/cli_reference.md > /tmp/co-017-mtimes-after.txt && diff /tmp/co-017-mtimes-before.txt /tmp/co-017-mtimes-after.txt && echo SENTINEL_MTIMES_OK` -> 5. `bash: jq -r 'select(.type == \"tool.call\") \\| .payload.name' /tmp/co-017-events.jsonl \\| grep -ciE '(Edit\\|Write)'` -> 6. `bash: jq -r 'select(.type == \"message.delta\" or .type == \"session.completed\") \\| .payload' /tmp/co-017-events.jsonl \\| grep -ciE '(big-bang\\|incremental wrapper\\|dual-build)'` -> 7. `bash: jq -r 'select(.type == \"message.delta\" or .type == \"session.completed\") \\| .payload' /tmp/co-017-events.jsonl \\| grep -ciE '(risk\\|effort\\|timeline\\|reversibility)'` -> 8. `bash: jq -r 'select(.type == \"message.delta\" or .type == \"session.completed\") \\| .payload' /tmp/co-017-events.jsonl \\| grep -ciE '(recommend\\|prefer\\|choose)'` | Step 1: sentinel mtimes captured; Step 2: events captured; Step 3: exit 0; Step 4: SENTINEL_MTIMES_OK printed; Step 5: count of Edit/Write tool.calls = 0; Step 6: count of strategy mentions >= 3; Step 7: count of dimension mentions >= 4; Step 8: at least one explicit recommendation phrase | `/tmp/co-017-events.jsonl`, `/tmp/co-017-mtimes-{before,after}.txt`, terminal grep counts | PASS if exit 0 AND SENTINEL_MTIMES_OK AND zero Edit/Write tool.calls AND >= 3 strategies AND >= 4 dimensions AND explicit recommendation; FAIL if any check fails | 1. If a sentinel mtime changed, the planning-only contract is violated — file a P0 LEAF safety regression; 2. If only 1-2 strategies appear, the agent collapsed to a linear plan — re-prompt with stronger \"produce 3 distinct strategies\" wording; 3. If dimensions are missing, add explicit \"score each on risk/effort/timeline/reversibility\" instructions; 4. If `--agent ai-council` is rejected (subagent, not top-level), confirm the request is going through `--agent orchestrate` instead |\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/references/agent_delegation.md:197:**Command-only (as of `mode: subagent`).** Direct `opencode run --agent ai-council` is no longer reachable — `ai-council.md` is `mode: subagent`, not directly selectable as a top-level session agent. Dispatch via `/deep:ai-council` for a full session, or via `opencode run --agent general \"...\"` and let `general`/`orchestrate`'s own routing Task-dispatch to `@ai-council` for a single planning pass.\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/references/agent_delegation.md:229:| Multi-strategy planning | `ai-council` | **Command-only.** Dispatch via `/deep:ai-council` for a full session, or `opencode run --agent general --variant high --format json --dir /repo \"Plan the authentication redesign — compare three strategies.\"` and let orchestrate's routing Task-dispatch `@ai-council`. Direct `opencode run --agent ai-council` is forbidden as of `mode: subagent`. |\n\n=== CLUSTER 2/3/4: .opencode/agents/*.toml across deep-loop tree + cli-opencode ===\n(zero .opencode/agents/*.toml hits in deep-loop+cli-opencode)\n\n=== CLUSTER 4: scan-integration.cjs MIRROR_TEMPLATES ===\n15:const MIRROR_TEMPLATES = [\n102:  return MIRROR_TEMPLATES.map((tpl) => {\n","exit":0,"truncated":false},"title":"echo \"=== CLUSTER 1: --agent ai-council across cli-opencode ===\"\nrg -n -- \"ai-council\" .opencode/skills/cli-opencode/ 2>/dev/null | rg -i \"agent|--agent|direct|invoke|dispatch\" || echo \"(no ai-council+agent hits in cli-opencode)\"\necho \"\"\necho \"=== CLUSTER 1b: --agent ai-council literal across cli-opencode ===\"\nrg -n -- \"--agent ai-council\" .opencode/skills/cli-opencode/ 2>/dev/null || echo \"(zero --agent ai-council literal hits)\"\necho \"\"\necho \"=== CLUSTER 2/3/4: .opencode/agents/*.toml across deep-loop tree + cli-opencode ===\"\nrg -n -- \"\\.opencode/agents/\\*\\.toml\" .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/ .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/ .opencode/skills/cli-opencode/ 2>/dev/null || echo \"(zero .opencode/agents/*.toml hits in deep-loop+cli-opencode)\"\necho \"\"\necho \"=== CLUSTER 4: scan-integration.cjs MIRROR_TEMPLATES ===\"\nrg -n -- \"MIRROR_TEMPLATES|\\.toml\" .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/scripts/agent-improvement/scan-integration.cjs 2>/dev/null || echo \"(no hits)\"","time":{"start":1782925209434,"end":1782925209436}},"id":"prt_f1e9faf1c001DpLydfB4C5jHZz","sessionID":"ses_0e161eb7effeWxawnzJ6Yp6rgG","messageID":"msg_f1e9f5e4a001KB5tV9osq7A3VZ"}}
