{"type":"text","timestamp":1782925280110,"sessionID":"ses_0e161eb7effeWxawnzJ6Yp6rgG","part":{"id":"prt_f1ea0c3600010gqzCgoSmm6GHv","messageID":"msg_f1ea0296f001rDgupGHxK6WnUS","sessionID":"ses_0e161eb7effeWxawnzJ6Yp6rgG","type":"text","text":"The 2-mirror model and REPO_ROOT fix are confirmed correct (6 `..` levels reaches repo root from the script's depth). Now let me broaden the scan repo-wide for residual `.toml` drift, verify the Cluster 6 wording reconciliation, and run the scanner smoke test + validate.sh.","time":{"start":1782925280096,"end":1782925280108}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782925280482,"sessionID":"ses_0e161eb7effeWxawnzJ6Yp6rgG","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"call_ce9588a715ec4df2bb290715","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"echo \"=== REPO-WIDE .opencode/agents/*.toml (beyond stated scope) ===\"\nrg -rn -- \"\\.opencode/agents/\\*\\.toml|agents/\\{name\\}\\.toml\" .opencode/ .claude/ AGENTS.md 2>/dev/null | rg -v \"node_modules\" | head -20 || echo \"(zero repo-wide)\"\necho \"\"\necho \"=== Broader: any '*.toml' mirror/agent reference in skills docs (non-changelog) ===\"\nrg -rn -- \"\\.toml\" .opencode/skills/ .claude/skills/ 2>/dev/null | rg -v \"node_modules|changelog/|target_manifest\" | rg -i \"agent|mirror\" | head -20 || echo \"(zero non-changelog .toml agent/mirror refs)\"\necho \"\"\necho \"=== Cluster 6: cli-opencode/SKILL.md lines 285-300 ===\"\nsed -n '285,300p' .opencode/skills/cli-opencode/SKILL.md 2>/dev/null","workdir":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public"},"output":"=== REPO-WIDE .opencode/agents/*.toml (beyond stated scope) ===\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/119-parent-skill-native-invocability/001-native-invocability-planning/review/iterations/iteration-010.md:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/references/agent_improvement/integration_scanning.md:46:| Codex mirror | `.codex/n` | Exists, sync status vs canonical |\n.opencode/specs/deep-loops/z_archive/012-sk-agent-improver-test-report-alignment/001-deep-research-recommendations/research/iterations/iteration-010.md:The mirror fix is not just a documentation cleanup; it is the first blocker in the ordered Call B chain because integration scoring depends on scanner output. `scan-integration.cjs` still hard-codes `.claude/agents/{name}.md`, `.codex/n`, and `.agents/agents/{name}.md` (`.opencode/skills/sk-improve-agent/scripts/scan-integration.cjs:15-19`). The scorer's integration dimension invokes that scanner and gives mirror parity 60% of the integration score (`.opencode/skills/sk-improve-agent/scripts/score-candidate.cjs:136-160`), matching the evaluator rubric's 0.25 Integration Consistency dimension and mirror/command/skill split (`.opencode/skills/sk-improve-agent/references/evaluator_contract.md:91-100`).\n.opencode/specs/deep-loops/z_archive/012-sk-agent-improver-test-report-alignment/001-deep-research-recommendations/research/iterations/iteration-010.md:  '.codex/n',\n.opencode/specs/deep-loops/z_archive/012-sk-agent-improver-test-report-alignment/001-deep-research-recommendations/research/iterations/iteration-010.md:  '.codex/n',\n.opencode/specs/deep-loops/z_archive/012-sk-agent-improver-test-report-alignment/001-deep-research-recommendations/research/iterations/iteration-002.md:The live scanner does not match the user-stated four runtime mirrors: it scans `.claude/agents/{name}.md`, `.codex/n`, and `.agents/agents/{name}.md`, not `.gemini/agents/{name}.md` (`.opencode/skills/sk-improve-agent/scripts/scan-integration.cjs:15-19`). Meanwhile the command note says runtime parity spans `.opencode`, `.claude`, `.codex`, and `.agents`, again not `.gemini` (`.opencode/commands/deep/start-agent-improvement-loop.md:400-406`). This is a concrete drift bug: documentation, user expectation, and scanner constants disagree.\n.opencode/specs/deep-loops/z_archive/012-sk-agent-improver-test-report-alignment/001-deep-research-recommendations/research/iterations/iteration-003.md:The executable scanner disagrees with that mirror list. `scan-integration.cjs` hard-codes `.claude/agents/{name}.md`, `.codex/n`, and `.agents/agents/{name}.md` as mirror templates (`.opencode/skills/sk-improve-agent/scripts/scan-integration.cjs:15-19`), and the command notes runtime parity across `.opencode`, `.claude`, `.codex`, and `.agents`, not `.gemini` (`.opencode/commands/deep/start-agent-improvement-loop.md:402-406`). `check-mirror-drift.cjs` can accept arbitrary `--mirrors=a,b,c` paths, but it relies on the caller to pass them and does not itself encode the four-runtime mirror contract (`.opencode/skills/sk-improve-agent/scripts/check-mirror-drift.cjs:51-63`, `.opencode/skills/sk-improve-agent/scripts/check-mirror-drift.cjs:118-143`).\n.opencode/specs/deep-loops/z_archive/012-sk-agent-improver-test-report-alignment/001-deep-research-recommendations/research/iterations/iteration-003.md:  '.codex/n',\n.opencode/specs/deep-loops/z_archive/012-sk-agent-improver-test-report-alignment/001-deep-research-recommendations/research/iterations/iteration-003.md:  '.codex/n',\n.opencode/specs/deep-loops/z_archive/012-sk-agent-improver-test-report-alignment/001-deep-research-recommendations/research/iterations/iteration-003.md:  '.codex/n',\n.opencode/specs/deep-loops/z_archive/012-sk-agent-improver-test-report-alignment/001-deep-research-recommendations/research/iterations/iteration-009.md:`scan-integration.cjs` hard-codes three mirror templates: `.claude/agents/{name}.md`, `.codex/n`, and `.agents/agents/{name}.md` (`.opencode/skills/sk-improve-agent/scripts/scan-integration.cjs:15-19`). The scanner then maps exactly those templates into `surfaces.mirrors` (`.opencode/skills/sk-improve-agent/scripts/scan-integration.cjs:105-110`) and summarizes missing/diverged mirrors from that list (`.opencode/skills/sk-improve-agent/scripts/scan-integration.cjs:196-227`). A read-only run for `improve-agent` reported `.claude` and `.codex` aligned, but `.agents/agents/improve-agent.md` missing; it did not report `.gemini/agents/improve-agent.md` even though that runtime mirror exists and has matching frontmatter (`.gemini/agents/improve-agent.md:1-20`, `.claude/agents/improve-agent.md:1-20`, `.codex/agents/improve-agent.toml:1-18`).\n.opencode/specs/deep-loops/z_archive/012-sk-agent-improver-test-report-alignment/001-deep-research-recommendations/research/iterations/iteration-009.md:  '.codex/n',\n.opencode/specs/deep-loops/z_archive/012-sk-agent-improver-test-report-alignment/001-deep-research-recommendations/research/iterations/iteration-009.md:  '.codex/n',\n.opencode/specs/deep-loops/z_archive/012-sk-agent-improver-test-report-alignment/001-deep-research-recommendations/research/iterations/iteration-009.md:  '.codex/n',\n.opencode/specs/deep-loops/z_archive/012-sk-agent-improver-test-report-alignment/001-deep-research-recommendations/research/research.md:**Recommended action:** Fix mirror inventory before legal-stop or score-gate work. Prefer an explicit runtime manifest consumed by `scan-integration.cjs`; if packet 061 keeps static defaults, use `.claude/agents/{name}.md`, `.codex/n`, and `.gemini/agents/{name}.md`, with `.agents/agents` only if manifest-declared.\n.opencode/specs/deep-loops/z_archive/023-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/002-implementation-deep-research/research/gpt55/logs/iter-004.out:    18\t  '.codex/n',\n.opencode/specs/deep-loops/z_archive/011-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/005-agent-improver-deep-loop-alignment/scratch/codex-gpt54-deep-research.md:  '.codex/n',\n.opencode/specs/deep-loops/z_archive/011-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-018.md:  '.codex/n',\n.opencode/specs/deep-loops/z_archive/021-deep-skill-evolution/005-deep-agent-improvement/001-research-recent-updates/research/iterations/iteration-008.md:- `feature_catalog/02--integration-scanning/02-runtime-mirrors.md:20`: \"currently checks `.claude/agents/{name}.md`, `.codex/n`, and `.agents/agents/{name}.md`\"\n.opencode/specs/deep-loops/z_archive/021-deep-skill-evolution/005-deep-agent-improvement/001-research-recent-updates/research/deltas/iter-008.jsonl:{\"id\":\"DAI-021\",\"severity\":\"P0\",\"category\":\"Documentation Drift\",\"title\":\"Mirror template drift in scan-integration.cjs\",\"location\":\".opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/scan-integration.cjs:15-19\",\"description\":\"The scanner's MIRROR_TEMPLATES array contains .gemini/agents/{name}.md, but multiple reference documents claim it checks .agents/agents/{name}.md instead.\",\"evidence\":[\"Actual code (line 18): '.gemini/agents/{name}.md'\",\"references/integration_scanning.md:39: '.agents mirror | .agents/agents/{name}.md'\",\"references/integration_scanning.md:78: example shows .agents/agents/{agent-name}.md\",\"feature_catalog/02--integration-scanning/02-runtime-mirrors.md:20: 'currently checks .claude/agents/{name}.md, .codex/n, and .agents/agents/{name}.md'\",\"manual_testing_playbook/01--integration-scanner/001-scan-known-agent.md:45: failure triage references .agents/agents\"],\"root_cause\":\"Documentation drift after mirror template changes. The code was updated to use .gemini/agents/ (correct path), but reference docs and test playbooks were not synchronized.\",\"impact\":[\"Operators are misled about which mirrors the scanner checks\",\"Manual testing playbook failure triage points to non-existent directory\",\"Breaks 'single source of truth' principle between code and docs\"],\"recommended_fix\":[\"Update references/integration_scanning.md table to show .gemini/agents/{name}.md instead of .agents/agents/{name}.md\",\"Update example output in same file\",\"Update feature_catalog/02--integration-scanning/02-runtime-mirrors.md to match actual code\",\"Update manual_testing_playbook/01--integration-scanner/001-scan-known-agent.md failure triage to reference .gemini/agents\"],\"iteration\":8,\"model\":\"SWE-1.6 (cli-devin)\"}\n.opencode/specs/deep-loops/z_archive/021-deep-skill-evolution/000-release-cleanup/013-deep-agent-improvement-release-cleanup/research/iterations/iteration-07.md:- scan-integration.cjs lines 15-20: `const MIRROR_TEMPLATES = ['.opencode/agents/{name}.md', '.claude/agents/{name}.md', '.codex/n', '.gemini/agents/{name}.md']` <ref_file file=\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/scan-integration.cjs\" lines=\"15-20\" />\n\n=== Broader: any '*.toml' mirror/agent reference in skills docs (non-changelog) ===\n.claude/skills/sk-code-review/manual_testing_playbook/04--scope-and-precedence/baseline-vs-surface-precedence.md:| CR-011 | Baseline vs surface precedence | Confirm surface conventions override generic process advice while baseline security and correctness remain mandatory. | `Review this diff against detected sk-code surface evidence, letting surface conventions win while baseline security and correctness still block.` | bash: git diff --staged --name-only -> agent: @review diff with sk-code surface evidence -> bash: rg -n -e \"package.json\" -e \"pyprojectn\" -e \"Cargon\" -e \"vite.config\" -e \"next.config\" . | Step 1: surface markers found; Step 2: report names surface evidence; Step 3: precedence is explicit | Surface marker transcript, final report baseline/surface lines | PASS if precedence follows references/review_core.md section 5 and SKILL.md precedence matrix; FAIL if generic baseline overrides surface-specific test commands | 1. Identify detected surface; 2. Load surface standards; 3. Separate style/process from security/correctness |\n.claude/skills/z_archive/cli-codex-retired/SKILL.retired.md:- **Agent-Delegated Tasks** — specialized profile matches (`.codex/agents/*n`), session management (resume, fork), multi-strategy planning.\n.claude/skills/z_archive/cli-codex-retired/SKILL.retired.md:**Profile setup**: Defined in `.codex/confign` under `[profiles.<name>]`. Each profile can override `model`, `model_reasoning_effort`, `sandbox_mode`, and `approval_policy`. The `.codex/agents/*n` files provide agent definitions for the interactive multi-agent TUI feature.\n.claude/skills/z_archive/cli-codex-retired/references/codex_tools.md:| **Agent system** | `.claude/agents/` | `.codex/agents/*n` | Both support specialized agents |\n.claude/skills/z_archive/cli-codex-retired/references/agent_delegation.md:Codex CLI tasks are routed using the `-p` / `--profile` flag with a profile name. Profiles are defined in `confign` under `[profiles.<name>]` sections. For git diff reviews, use the built-in `codex exec review` subcommand.\n.claude/skills/z_archive/cli-codex-retired/references/agent_delegation.md:Profiles must be defined in `confign`. Example configuration matching the agent catalog below:\n.claude/skills/z_archive/cli-codex-retired/references/agent_delegation.md:# .codex/confign\n.claude/skills/z_archive/cli-codex-retired/references/agent_delegation.md:**Note:** The `.codex/agents/*n` files define agent personas for the interactive multi-agent TUI feature. They are NOT loaded by the `-p` profile flag. To use agent-specific behavior in `codex exec`, define corresponding `[profiles.<name>]` sections in confign and include context in the prompt.\n.claude/skills/z_archive/cli-codex-retired/references/agent_delegation.md:| Profile not found   | Error: profile not defined          | Verify profile name matches `[profiles.<name>]` in confign |\n.claude/skills/z_archive/cli-codex-retired/README.md:Route to a specialized Codex agent through the repo-local agent surface. `.codex/confign` declares `[agents.<name>]` entries whose `config_file` values point at `.codex/agents/<name>n`; the `.codex/agents/` directory holds the Codex-side agent files. The roster is larger than the old six-profile set.\n.claude/skills/z_archive/cli-codex-retired/references/cli_reference.md:- Configuring agents via `.codex/agents/*n`\n.claude/skills/z_archive/cli-codex-retired/references/cli_reference.md:# .codex/agents/my-agentn — reasoning-heavy agent\n.claude/skills/z_archive/cli-codex-retired/references/cli_reference.md:# .codex/agents/my-codegen-agentn — code-focused agent\n.claude/skills/z_archive/cli-codex-retired/references/cli_reference.md:Each agent is a `n` file in `.codex/agents/`. Fields:\n.claude/skills/z_archive/cli-codex-retired/references/cli_reference.md:# .codex/agents/examplen\n.claude/skills/z_archive/cli-codex-retired/references/cli_reference.md:**Note:** The `.codex/agents/*n` files define agent personas for the interactive multi-agent TUI feature (requires `multi_agent` feature flag). They are NOT loaded by the `-p` profile flag. To use agent-specific settings in `codex exec`, define corresponding `[profiles.<name>]` sections in confign.\n.claude/skills/z_archive/cli-codex-retired/manual_testing_playbook/04--agent-routing/research-profile.md:| CX-026 | @research profile (web-grounded investigation) | Verify -p research --search returns a citation-backed comparative analysis with a recommendation | `As a cross-AI orchestrator delegating an evidence-backed investigation, dispatch codex exec -p research --search --model gpt-5.5 -c model_reasoning_effort=\"high\" -c service_tier=\"fast\" --sandbox read-only \"Compare current Bun and Deno major releases across runtime performance, package ecosystem, and operational stability. Cite at least one HTTPS source URL per candidate. End with a recommendation plus rationale.\" Verify the dispatch routes via -p research, cites at least 2 HTTPS URLs, names both candidates with explicit pros and cons, and ends with a recommendation. Return a verdict naming the cited URLs, the trade-off dimensions covered, and the recommendation.` | 1. `codex exec -p research --search --model gpt-5.5 -c model_reasoning_effort=\"high\" -c service_tier=\"fast\" --sandbox read-only \"Compare current Bun and Deno major releases across runtime performance, package ecosystem, and operational stability. Cite at least one HTTPS source URL per candidate. End with a recommendation plus rationale.\" </dev/null > /tmp/cli-codex-cx026.txt 2>&1` -> 2. `bash: echo \"Exit: $?\"` -> 3. `bash: grep -ciE '(bun\\|deno)' /tmp/cli-codex-cx026.txt` -> 4. `bash: grep -ciE '(performance\\|ecosystem\\|stability)' /tmp/cli-codex-cx026.txt` -> 5. `bash: grep -oE 'https://[a-zA-Z0-9./_-]+' /tmp/cli-codex-cx026.txt \\| sort -u \\| wc -l \\| tr -d ' '` -> 6. `bash: grep -ciE '(recommend\\|recommendation)' /tmp/cli-codex-cx026.txt` | Step 1: dispatch captured; Step 2: exit 0; Step 3: count of candidate mentions >= 4 (each candidate >= 2 times); Step 4: count of dimension mentions >= 3; Step 5: distinct HTTPS URL count >= 2; Step 6: recommendation count >= 1 | `/tmp/cli-codex-cx026.txt`, terminal exit code, grep counts, URL count | PASS if exit 0 AND >= 2 candidates AND >= 3 dimensions AND >= 2 HTTPS URLs AND recommendation present AND `-p research` plus `--search` in dispatch; FAIL if any check misses | (1) Define `[profiles.research]` in confign if missing per agent_delegation.md §3 (sandbox_mode = \"workspace-write\" but the profile here uses --sandbox read-only as the override); (2) re-run after `codex login` if rate limits or auth errors surface; (3) if URL count is 0, --search may not have engaged, capture stderr and check for `--search` recognition |\n.claude/skills/z_archive/cli-codex-retired/manual_testing_playbook/04--agent-routing/research-profile.md:| `.codex/confign` (or `~/.codex/confign`) | `[profiles.research]` section |\n.claude/skills/z_archive/cli-codex-retired/manual_testing_playbook/04--agent-routing/review-profile.md:- Expected execution process: Operator confirms `.codex/confign` has a `[profiles.review]` section -> snapshots `git status --porcelain` -> dispatches with `-p review` -> captures stdout -> verifies categorized findings -> re-snapshots and confirms no diffs.\n.claude/skills/z_archive/cli-codex-retired/manual_testing_playbook/04--agent-routing/review-profile.md:1. Confirm `.codex/confign` has a `[profiles.review]` section (or note that the profile must be created per `agent_delegation.md` §2 Profile Setup).\n\n=== Cluster 6: cli-opencode/SKILL.md lines 285-300 ===\nOpenCode defines `general`, `plan`, and `orchestrate` as primary agents. **Caveat — never pass `--agent general`:** the current opencode treats `general` as a subagent and rejects it at the top level, and the default agent (used when no `--agent` is given) already covers that case. Pin `--agent plan|orchestrate` only when the task needs that profile AND `opencode run --help` on the installed version confirms top-level acceptance; otherwise state the role in the prompt body.\n\n#### Subagents — dispatched as Task subagents from a primary\n\nThese live at `.opencode/agents/<slug>.md` with `mode: subagent` and are NOT directly invokable via `opencode run --agent`. Three dispatch surfaces are legal under the single-hop NDP contract:\n\n1. **Generic subagents** (`context`, `review`, `write`, `debug`) — dispatched by a primary (`orchestrate`) using the Task tool. To exercise via the opencode CLI, route through `--agent orchestrate` and let it dispatch the relevant subagent.\n2. **`ai-council`** — dispatched either via its own `/deep:ai-council` command or via `orchestrate`'s registry-backed Task-dispatch. Direct `--agent ai-council` is rejected at the top level (`mode: subagent`); route through `/deep:ai-council` or `--agent orchestrate` with an ai-council-shaped prompt.\n3. **Command-owned loop executors** (`deep-research`, `deep-review`, `deep-improvement`, `prompt-improver`) — LOOP-OWNED by their parent commands (`/deep:research`, `/deep:review`, `/deep:agent-improvement`, `/prompt`), which own iteration state, convergence detection, and continuity. Never dispatch these directly via raw `--agent <slug>` from the CLI. `orchestrate` is an authorized **caller/coordinator only** for these agents (e.g. its registry-backed `/deep:review` Priority row) — it may perform exactly one bounded hand-off dispatch to the resolved leaf, but MUST NOT re-implement the loop (no iterating, no convergence checks, no continuity tracking); that remains the parent command's job.\n\nGeneric subagents (`context`, `review`, `write`, `debug`) and `ai-council` route through `orchestrate` for full Task-tool dispatch; loop executors (`deep-research`, `deep-review`, `deep-improvement`, `prompt-improver`) are loop-owned by their parent commands, with `orchestrate` limited to a single bounded hand-off when it recognizes one of these as the target.\n\nSee [agent_delegation.md](./references/agent_delegation.md) for the complete agent roster and dispatch patterns.\n\n### Unique OpenCode Strengths\n\n","metadata":{"output":"=== REPO-WIDE .opencode/agents/*.toml (beyond stated scope) ===\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/119-parent-skill-native-invocability/001-native-invocability-planning/review/iterations/iteration-010.md:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/references/agent_improvement/integration_scanning.md:46:| Codex mirror | `.codex/n` | Exists, sync status vs canonical |\n.opencode/specs/deep-loops/z_archive/012-sk-agent-improver-test-report-alignment/001-deep-research-recommendations/research/iterations/iteration-010.md:The mirror fix is not just a documentation cleanup; it is the first blocker in the ordered Call B chain because integration scoring depends on scanner output. `scan-integration.cjs` still hard-codes `.claude/agents/{name}.md`, `.codex/n`, and `.agents/agents/{name}.md` (`.opencode/skills/sk-improve-agent/scripts/scan-integration.cjs:15-19`). The scorer's integration dimension invokes that scanner and gives mirror parity 60% of the integration score (`.opencode/skills/sk-improve-agent/scripts/score-candidate.cjs:136-160`), matching the evaluator rubric's 0.25 Integration Consistency dimension and mirror/command/skill split (`.opencode/skills/sk-improve-agent/references/evaluator_contract.md:91-100`).\n.opencode/specs/deep-loops/z_archive/012-sk-agent-improver-test-report-alignment/001-deep-research-recommendations/research/iterations/iteration-010.md:  '.codex/n',\n.opencode/specs/deep-loops/z_archive/012-sk-agent-improver-test-report-alignment/001-deep-research-recommendations/research/iterations/iteration-010.md:  '.codex/n',\n.opencode/specs/deep-loops/z_archive/012-sk-agent-improver-test-report-alignment/001-deep-research-recommendations/research/iterations/iteration-002.md:The live scanner does not match the user-stated four runtime mirrors: it scans `.claude/agents/{name}.md`, `.codex/n`, and `.agents/agents/{name}.md`, not `.gemini/agents/{name}.md` (`.opencode/skills/sk-improve-agent/scripts/scan-integration.cjs:15-19`). Meanwhile the command note says runtime parity spans `.opencode`, `.claude`, `.codex`, and `.agents`, again not `.gemini` (`.opencode/commands/deep/start-agent-improvement-loop.md:400-406`). This is a concrete drift bug: documentation, user expectation, and scanner constants disagree.\n.opencode/specs/deep-loops/z_archive/012-sk-agent-improver-test-report-alignment/001-deep-research-recommendations/research/iterations/iteration-003.md:The executable scanner disagrees with that mirror list. `scan-integration.cjs` hard-codes `.claude/agents/{name}.md`, `.codex/n`, and `.agents/agents/{name}.md` as mirror templates (`.opencode/skills/sk-improve-agent/scripts/scan-integration.cjs:15-19`), and the command notes runtime parity across `.opencode`, `.claude`, `.codex`, and `.agents`, not `.gemini` (`.opencode/commands/deep/start-agent-improvement-loop.md:402-406`). `check-mirror-drift.cjs` can accept arbitrary `--mirrors=a,b,c` paths, but it relies on the caller to pass them and does not itself encode the four-runtime mirror contract (`.opencode/skills/sk-improve-agent/scripts/check-mirror-drift.cjs:51-63`, `.opencode/skills/sk-improve-agent/scripts/check-mirror-drift.cjs:118-143`).\n.opencode/specs/deep-loops/z_archive/012-sk-agent-improver-test-report-alignment/001-deep-research-recommendations/research/iterations/iteration-003.md:  '.codex/n',\n.opencode/specs/deep-loops/z_archive/012-sk-agent-improver-test-report-alignment/001-deep-research-recommendations/research/iterations/iteration-003.md:  '.codex/n',\n.opencode/specs/deep-loops/z_archive/012-sk-agent-improver-test-report-alignment/001-deep-research-recommendations/research/iterations/iteration-003.md:  '.codex/n',\n.opencode/specs/deep-loops/z_archive/012-sk-agent-improver-test-report-alignment/001-deep-research-recommendations/research/iterations/iteration-009.md:`scan-integration.cjs` hard-codes three mirror templates: `.claude/agents/{name}.md`, `.codex/n`, and `.agents/agents/{name}.md` (`.opencode/skills/sk-improve-agent/scripts/scan-integration.cjs:15-19`). The scanner then maps exactly those templates into `surfaces.mirrors` (`.opencode/skills/sk-improve-agent/scripts/scan-integration.cjs:105-110`) and summarizes missing/diverged mirrors from that list (`.opencode/skills/sk-improve-agent/scripts/scan-integration.cjs:196-227`). A read-only run for `improve-agent` reported `.claude` and `.codex` aligned, but `.agents/agents/improve-agent.md` missing; it did not report `.gemini/agents/improve-agent.md` even though that runtime mirror exists and has matching frontmatter (`.gemini/agents/improve-agent.md:1-20`, `.claude/agents/improve-agent.md:1-20`, `.codex/agents/improve-agent.toml:1-18`).\n.opencode/specs/deep-loops/z_archive/012-sk-agent-improver-test-report-alignment/001-deep-research-recommendations/research/iterations/iteration-009.md:  '.codex/n',\n.opencode/specs/deep-loops/z_archive/012-sk-agent-improver-test-report-alignment/001-deep-research-recommendations/research/iterations/iteration-009.md:  '.codex/n',\n.opencode/specs/deep-loops/z_archive/012-sk-agent-improver-test-report-alignment/001-deep-research-recommendations/research/iterations/iteration-009.md:  '.codex/n',\n.opencode/specs/deep-loops/z_archive/012-sk-agent-improver-test-report-alignment/001-deep-research-recommendations/research/research.md:**Recommended action:** Fix mirror inventory before legal-stop or score-gate work. Prefer an explicit runtime manifest consumed by `scan-integration.cjs`; if packet 061 keeps static defaults, use `.claude/agents/{name}.md`, `.codex/n`, and `.gemini/agents/{name}.md`, with `.agents/agents` only if manifest-declared.\n.opencode/specs/deep-loops/z_archive/023-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/002-implementation-deep-research/research/gpt55/logs/iter-004.out:    18\t  '.codex/n',\n.opencode/specs/deep-loops/z_archive/011-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/005-agent-improver-deep-loop-alignment/scratch/codex-gpt54-deep-research.md:  '.codex/n',\n.opencode/specs/deep-loops/z_archive/011-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-018.md:  '.codex/n',\n.opencode/specs/deep-loops/z_archive/021-deep-skill-evolution/005-deep-agent-improvement/001-research-recent-updates/research/iterations/iteration-008.md:- `feature_catalog/02--integration-scanning/02-runtime-mirrors.md:20`: \"currently checks `.claude/agents/{name}.md`, `.codex/n`, and `.agents/agents/{name}.md`\"\n.opencode/specs/deep-loops/z_archive/021-deep-skill-evolution/005-deep-agent-improvement/001-research-recent-updates/research/deltas/iter-008.jsonl:{\"id\":\"DAI-021\",\"severity\":\"P0\",\"category\":\"Documentation Drift\",\"title\":\"Mirror template drift in scan-integration.cjs\",\"location\":\".opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/scan-integration.cjs:15-19\",\"description\":\"The scanner's MIRROR_TEMPLATES array contains .gemini/agents/{name}.md, but multiple reference documents claim it checks .agents/agents/{name}.md instead.\",\"evidence\":[\"Actual code (line 18): '.gemini/agents/{name}.md'\",\"references/integration_scanning.md:39: '.agents mirror | .agents/agents/{name}.md'\",\"references/integration_scanning.md:78: example shows .agents/agents/{agent-name}.md\",\"feature_catalog/02--integration-scanning/02-runtime-mirrors.md:20: 'currently checks .claude/agents/{name}.md, .codex/n, and .agents/agents/{name}.md'\",\"manual_testing_playbook/01--integration-scanner/001-scan-known-agent.md:45: failure triage references .agents/agents\"],\"root_cause\":\"Documentation drift after mirror template changes. The code was updated to use .gemini/agents/ (correct path), but reference docs and test playbooks were not synchronized.\",\"impact\":[\"Operators are misled about which mirrors the scanner checks\",\"Manual testing playbook failure triage points to non-existent directory\",\"Breaks 'single source of tr