{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782925344924,"sessionID":"ses_0e161eb7effeWxawnzJ6Yp6rgG","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"call_cf7f2afa64f142f58d8f1a83","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"echo \"=== ai-council actual mode (ground truth) ===\"\nrg -n -- \"^mode:|^name:\" .opencode/agents/ai-council.md 2>/dev/null || echo \"(no .opencode/agents/ai-council.md)\"\necho \"\"\necho \"=== Does .claude/agents/ mirror exist for deep-loop agents? (2-mirror model claim) ===\"\nls -1 .claude/agents/ 2>/dev/null | rg \"deep-review|deep-research|ai-council|deep-context|deep-improvement\" || echo \"(no deep-loop mirrors in .claude/agents/)\"\necho \"\"\necho \"=== Taxonomy contradiction check: is ai-council 'primary' or 'subagent' in cli-opencode living docs? ===\"\nrg -n -- \"ai-council.*primary|primary.*ai-council|ai-council.*repo-defined primar\" .opencode/skills/cli-opencode/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md 2>/dev/null\necho \"---SKILL.md primary list---\"\nsed -n '285p' .opencode/skills/cli-opencode/SKILL.md 2>/dev/null\necho \"\"\necho \"=== orchestrate.md @deep-review row (Cluster 6 claim: untouched, load-bearing) ===\"\nrg -n -- \"deep-review|Priority|@deep\" .opencode/agents/orchestrate.md 2>/dev/null | head -8","workdir":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public"},"output":"=== ai-council actual mode (ground truth) ===\n2:name: ai-council\n4:mode: subagent\n\n=== Does .claude/agents/ mirror exist for deep-loop agents? (2-mirror model claim) ===\nai-council.md\ndeep-context.md\ndeep-improvement.md\ndeep-research.md\ndeep-review.md\n\n=== Taxonomy contradiction check: is ai-council 'primary' or 'subagent' in cli-opencode living docs? ===\n362:This category covers 8 scenario summaries while the linked feature files remain the canonical execution contract. cli-opencode distinguishes 4 primary agents (directly invokable via --agent: general + plan as OpenCode built-ins; orchestrate + ai-council as repo-defined primaries) from N subagents (context, review, write, debug, deep-research, deep-review, deep-improvement, prompt-improver) which dispatch as Task subagents from a primary. CO-013..CO-017 + CO-032..CO-034 exercise both surfaces — direct primary invocation and primary-dispatches-subagent routing.\n---SKILL.md primary list---\nOpenCode defines `general`, `plan`, and `orchestrate` as primary agents. **Caveat — never pass `--agent general`:** the current opencode treats `general` as a subagent and rejects it at the top level, and the default agent (used when no `--agent` is given) already covers that case. Pin `--agent plan|orchestrate` only when the task needs that profile AND `opencode run --help` on the installed version confirms top-level acceptance; otherwise state the role in the prompt body.\n\n=== orchestrate.md @deep-review row (Cluster 6 claim: untouched, load-bearing) ===\n69:### Agent Selection (Priority Order)\n71:| Priority | Task Type                                                                 | Agent                  | Tier | Skills                                                                            | subagent_type |\n74:| 2        | Deep-loop iterative context-gathering sweep (`/deep:context` only — explicit deep-loop convergence request, not general exploration) | `@deep-context` | LEAF | `system-spec-kit`, `deep-context` | `\"general\"` |\n75:| 3        | Evidence / iterative investigation                                        | `@deep-research`       | LEAF | `system-spec-kit`, `deep-research`                                             | `\"general\"`   |\n79:| 7        | Deep-loop iterative code-audit pass (`/deep:review` only — explicit deep-loop convergence request, not a one-shot review) | `@deep-review` | LEAF | `system-spec-kit`, `deep-review` | `\"general\"` |\n92:| **LEAF**         | MUST NOT dispatch any sub-agents | @context, @code, @markdown, @ai-council, @review, @debug, @deep-context, @deep-research, @deep-review |\n125:ILLEGAL: Orch(0) → @deep(1)  [@deep is mode: primary, not a depth-1 leaf -- it self-routes and would itself need to dispatch a leaf at depth 2]\n128:**@deep is never a Task-dispatch target for this orchestrator.** For `/deep:*` requests, resolve the target leaf agent directly from the Priority table above (registry-backed) and dispatch that leaf at depth 1. Never Task-dispatch `@deep` itself as a worker — it is a primary router, and doing so would create the illegal `Orch(0) → @deep(1) → @leaf(2)` chain.\n","metadata":{"output":"=== ai-council actual mode (ground truth) ===\n2:name: ai-council\n4:mode: subagent\n\n=== Does .claude/agents/ mirror exist for deep-loop agents? (2-mirror model claim) ===\nai-council.md\ndeep-context.md\ndeep-improvement.md\ndeep-research.md\ndeep-review.md\n\n=== Taxonomy contradiction check: is ai-council 'primary' or 'subagent' in cli-opencode living docs? ===\n362:This category covers 8 scenario summaries while the linked feature files remain the canonical execution contract. cli-opencode distinguishes 4 primary agents (directly invokable via --agent: general + plan as OpenCode built-ins; orchestrate + ai-council as repo-defined primaries) from N subagents (context, review, write, debug, deep-research, deep-review, deep-improvement, prompt-improver) which dispatch as Task subagents from a primary. CO-013..CO-017 + CO-032..CO-034 exercise both surfaces — direct primary invocation and primary-dispatches-subagent routing.\n---SKILL.md primary list---\nOpenCode defines `general`, `plan`, and `orchestrate` as primary agents. **Caveat — never pass `--agent general`:** the current opencode treats `general` as a subagent and rejects it at the top level, and the default agent (used when no `--agent` is given) already covers that case. Pin `--agent plan|orchestrate` only when the task needs that profile AND `opencode run --help` on the installed version confirms top-level acceptance; otherwise state the role in the prompt body.\n\n=== orchestrate.md @deep-review row (Cluster 6 claim: untouched, load-bearing) ===\n69:### Agent Selection (Priority Order)\n71:| Priority | Task Type                                                                 | Agent                  | Tier | Skills                                                                            | subagent_type |\n74:| 2        | Deep-loop iterative context-gathering sweep (`/deep:context` only — explicit deep-loop convergence request, not general exploration) | `@deep-context` | LEAF | `system-spec-kit`, `deep-context` | `\"general\"` |\n75:| 3        | Evidence / iterative investigation                                        | `@deep-research`       | LEAF | `system-spec-kit`, `deep-research`                                             | `\"general\"`   |\n79:| 7        | Deep-loop iterative code-audit pass (`/deep:review` only — explicit deep-loop convergence request, not a one-shot review) | `@deep-review` | LEAF | `system-spec-kit`, `deep-review` | `\"general\"` |\n92:| **LEAF**         | MUST NOT dispatch any sub-agents | @context, @code, @markdown, @ai-council, @review, @debug, @deep-context, @deep-research, @deep-review |\n125:ILLEGAL: Orch(0) → @deep(1)  [@deep is mode: primary, not a depth-1 leaf -- it self-routes and would itself need to dispatch a leaf at depth 2]\n128:**@deep is never a Task-dispatch target for this orchestrator.** For `/deep:*` requests, resolve the target leaf agent directly from the Priority table above (registry-backed) and dispatch that leaf at depth 1. Never Task-dispatch `@deep` itself as a worker — it is a primary router, and doing so would create the illegal `Orch(0) → @deep(1) → @leaf(2)` chain.\n","exit":0,"truncated":false},"title":"echo \"=== ai-council actual mode (ground truth) ===\"\nrg -n -- \"^mode:|^name:\" .opencode/agents/ai-council.md 2>/dev/null || echo \"(no .opencode/agents/ai-council.md)\"\necho \"\"\necho \"=== Does .claude/agents/ mirror exist for deep-loop agents? (2-mirror model claim)