out as the session runs, ending with a final tool-result message. The `</dev/null` is mandatory on non-interactive runs. Do not pass top-level `--agent` by default: `context`, `review`, `debug`, and `n agents such as `plan` or `orchestrate` after `opencode run --help` confirms acceptance.\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/README.md:| `--agent general` fails or warns | The default/general path is selected by omitting `--agent` | Omit `--agent general`; use `orchestrate` only when it is the documented n`) instead of direct top-level `--agent` examples. |\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md:This category covers 8 scenario summaries while the linked feature files remain the canonical execution contract. cli-opencode distinguishes 4 n as repo-defined primaries) from N subagents (context, review, write, debug, deep-research, deep-review, deep-improvement, prompt-improver) which dispatch as Task subagents from a primary. CO-013..CO-017 + CO-032..CO-034 exercise both surfaces — direct primary invocation and primary-dispatches-subagent routing.\n","metadata":{"output":"=== Residual .toml in deep-research/deep-review/deep-ai-council playbooks (T013 claimed fixed) ===\n(zero .toml in those playbooks — T013 holds)\n\n=== Residual 'directly invokable' / 'primary' ai-council claims across ALL cli-opencode living docs ===\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/SKILL.md:- **Agent dispatch** — task matches a specialized OpenCode agent. Primary agents (directly invokable via `--agent`): `general`, `plan` (built-in), `orchestrate`. Generic subagents fully dispatched via the orchestrate n`. Command-owned loop executors (`deep-research`, `deep-review`, `deep-improvement`, `prompt-improver`) are owned end-to-end by their parent `/deep:*` command; `orchestrate` may perform exactly one bounded hand-off dispatch to a recognized loop request, but never manages the loop itself. See §3 \"OpenCode Agent Delegation\" for the full contract.\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/README.md:You get structured JSON events streamed to stdout as the session runs, ending with a final tool-result message. The `</dev/null` is mandatory on non-interactive runs. Do not pass top-level `--agent` by default: `context`, `review`, `debug`, and `n agents such as `plan` or `orchestrate` after `opencode run --help` confirms acceptance.\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/README.md:| `--agent general` fails or warns | The default/general path is selected by omitting `--agent` | Omit `--agent general`; use `orchestrate` only when it is the documented n`) instead of direct top-level `--agent` examples. |\n.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md:This category covers 8 scenario summaries while the linked feature files remain the canonical execution contract. cli-opencode distinguishes 4 n as repo-defined primaries) from N subagents (context, review, write, debug, deep-research, deep-review, deep-improvement, prompt-improver) which dispatch as Task subagents from a primary. CO-013..CO-017 + CO-032..CO-034 exercise both surfaces — direct primary invocation and primary-dispatches-subagent routing.\n","exit":0,"truncated":false},"title":"echo \"=== Residual .toml in deep-research/deep-review/deep-ai-council playbooks (T013 claimed fixed) ===\"\nrg -rn -- \"\\.toml\" .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/manual_testing_playbook/ .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/manual_testing_playbook/ .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/manual_testing_playbook/ 2>/dev/null || echo \"(zero .toml in those playbooks — T013 holds)\"\necho \"\"\necho \"=== Residual 'directly invokable' / 'primary' ai-council claims across ALL cli-opencode living docs ===\"\nrg -rn -- \"ai-council.*primary|primary.*ai-council\" .opencode/skills/cli-opencode/ 2>/dev/null | rg -v \"node_modules|changelog\" || echo \"(no ai-council+primary claims outside changelog)\"","time":{"start":1782925489657,"end":1782925489658}}